19Ps 42:3 My tears have been my food day and night, while men say to me all day long, "Where is your God?"
19Ps 42:4 These things I remember as I pour out my soul£º how I used to go with the multitude, leading the procession to the house of God, with shouts of joy and thanksgiving among the festive throng.
19Ps 42:5 Why are you downcast, O my soul? Why so disturbed within me? Put your hope in God, for I will yet praise him, my Savior and
19Ps 42:6 my God. My soul is downcast within me; therefore I will remember you from the land of the Jordan, the heights of Hermon--from Mount Mizar.
19Ps 42:7 Deep calls to deep in the roar of your waterfalls; all your waves and breakers have swept over me.
19Ps 42:8 By day the LORD directs his love, at night his song is with me--a prayer to the God of my life.
19Ps 42:9 I say to God my Rock, "Why have you forgotten me? Why must I go about mourning, oppressed by the enemy?"
19Ps 42:10 My bones suffer mortal agony as my foes taunt me, saying to me all day long, "Where is your God?"
19Ps 42:11 Why are you downcast, O my soul? Why so disturbed within me? Put your hope in God, for I will yet praise him, my Savior and my God.
19Ps 43:1 Vindicate me, O God, and plead my cause against an ungodly nation; rescue me from deceitful and wicked men.
19Ps 43:2 You are God my stronghold. Why have you rejected me? Why must I go about mourning, oppressed by the enemy?
19Ps 43:3 Send forth your light and your truth, let them guide me; let them bring me to your holy mountain, to the place where you dwell.
19Ps 43:4 Then will I go to the altar of God, to God, my joy and my delight. I will praise you with the harp, O God, my God.
19Ps 43:5 Why are you downcast, O my soul? Why so disturbed within me? Put your hope in God, for I will yet praise him, my Savior and my God.
19Ps 44:1 For the director of music. Of the Sons of Korah. A maskil. We have heard with our ears, O God; our fathers have told us what you did in their days, in days long ago.
19Ps 44:2 With your hand you drove out the nations and planted our fathers; you crushed the peoples and made our fathers flourish.
19Ps 44:3 It was not by their sword that they won the land, nor did their arm bring them victory; it was your right hand, your arm, and the light of your face, for you loved them.
19Ps 44:4 You are my King and my God, who decrees victories for Jacob.
19Ps 44:5 Through you we push back our enemies; through your name we trample our foes.
19Ps 44:6 I do not trust in my bow, my sword does not bring me victory;
