19Ps 45:9 Daughters of kings are among your honored women; at your right hand is the royal bride in gold of Ophir.
19Ps 45:10 Listen, O daughter, consider and give ear£º Forget your people and your father's house.
19Ps 45:11 The king is enthralled by your beauty; honor him, for he is your lord.
19Ps 45:12 The Daughter of Tyre will come with a gift, men of wealth will seek your favor.
19Ps 45:13 All glorious is the princess within her chamber; her gown is interwoven with gold.
19Ps 45:14 In embroidered garments she is led to the king; her virgin companions follow her and are brought to you.
19Ps 45:15 They are led in with joy and gladness; they enter the palace of the king.
19Ps 45:16 Your sons will take the place of your fathers; you will make them princes throughout the land.
19Ps 45:17 I will perpetuate your memory through all generations; therefore the nations will praise you for ever and ever.
19Ps 46:1 For the director of music. Of the Sons of Korah. According to alamoth. A song. God is our refuge and strength, an ever-present help in trouble.
19Ps 46:2 Therefore we will not fear, though the earth give way and the mountains fall into the heart of the sea,
19Ps 46:3 though its waters roar and foam and the mountains quake with their surging. Selah
19Ps 46:4 There is a river whose streams make glad the city of God, the holy place where the Most High dwells.
19Ps 46:5 God is within her, she will not fall; God will help her at break of day.
19Ps 46:6 Nations are in uproar, kingdoms fall; he lifts his voice, the earth melts.
19Ps 46:7 The LORD Almighty is with us; the God of Jacob is our fortress. Selah
19Ps 46:8 Come and see the works of the LORD, the desolations he has brought on the earth.
19Ps 46:9 He makes wars cease to the ends of the earth; he breaks the bow and shatters the spear, he burns the shields with fire.
19Ps 46:10 "Be still, and know that I am God; I will be exalted among the nations, I will be exalted in the earth."
19Ps 46:11 The LORD Almighty is with us; the God of Jacob is our fortress. Selah
19Ps 47:1 For the director of music. Of the Sons of Korah. A psalm. Clap your hands, all you nations; shout to God with cries of joy.
19Ps 47:2 How awesome is the LORD Most High, the great King over all the earth!
19Ps 47:3 He subdued nations under us, peoples under our feet.
19Ps 47:4 He chose our inheritance for us, the pride of Jacob, whom he loved. Selah
19Ps 47:5 God has ascended amid shouts of joy, the LORD amid the sounding of trumpets.
19Ps 47:6 Sing praises to God, sing praises; sing praises to our King, sing praises.
19Ps 47:7 For God is the King of all the earth; sing to him a psalm of praise.
19Ps 47:8 God reigns over the nations; God is seated on his holy throne.
19Ps 47:9 The nobles of the nations assemble as the people of the God of Abraham, for the kings of the earth belong to God; he is greatly exalted.
19Ps 48:1 A song. A psalm of the Sons of Korah. Great is the LORD, and most worthy of praise, in the city of our God, his holy mountain.
19Ps 48:2 It is beautiful in its loftiness, the joy of the whole earth. Like the utmost heights of Zaphon is Mount Zion, the city of the Great King.
19Ps 48:3 God is in her citadels; he has shown himself to be her fortress.
19Ps 48:4 When the kings joined forces, when they advanced together,
19Ps 48:5 they saw her and were astounded; they fled in terror.
19Ps 48:6 Trembling seized them there, pain like that of a woman in labor.
19Ps 48:7 You destroyed them like ships of Tarshish shattered by an east wind.
19Ps 48:8 As we have heard, so have we seen in the city of the LORD Almighty, in the city of our God£º God makes her secure forever. Selah
19Ps 48:9 Within your temple, O God, we meditate on your unfailing love.
19Ps 48:10 Like your name, O God, your praise reaches to the ends of the earth; your right hand is filled with righteousness.
19Ps 48:11 Mount Zion rejoices, the villages of Judah are glad because of your judgments.
19Ps 48:12 Walk about Zion, go around her, count her towers,
19Ps 48:13 consider well her ramparts, view her citadels, that you may tell of them to the next generation.
19Ps 48:14 For this God is our God for ever and ever; he will be our guide even to the end.
19Ps 49:1 For the director of music. Of the Sons of Korah. A psalm. Hear this, all you peoples; listen, all who live in this world,
19Ps 49:2 both low and high, rich and poor alike£º
19Ps 49:3 My mouth will speak words of wisdom; the utterance from my heart will give understanding.
19Ps 49:4 I will turn my ear to a proverb; with the harp I will expound my riddle£º
19Ps 49:5 Why should I fear when evil days come, when wicked deceivers surround me--
19Ps 49:6 those who trust in their wealth and boast of their great riches?
19Ps 49:7 No man can redeem the life of another or give to God a ransom for him--
19Ps 49:8 the ransom for a life is costly, no payment is ever enough--
19Ps 49:9 that he should live on forever and not see decay.
19Ps 49:10 For all can see that wise men die; the foolish and the senseless alike perish and leave their wealth to others.
19Ps 49:11 Their tombs will remain their houses forever, their dwellings for endless generations, though they had named lands after themselves.
19Ps 49:12 But man, despite his riches, does not endure; he is like the beasts that perish.
19Ps 49:13 This is the fate of those who trust in themselves, and of their followers, who approve their sayings. Selah
19Ps 49:14 Like sheep they are destined for the grave, and death will feed on them. The upright will rule over them in the morning; their forms will decay in the grave, far from their princely mansions.
19Ps 49:15 But God will redeem my life from the grave; he will surely take me to himself. Selah
19Ps 49:16 Do not be overawed when a man grows rich, when the splendor of his house increases;
19Ps 49:17 for he will take nothing with him when he dies, his splendor will not descend with him.
19Ps 49:18 Though while he lived he counted himself blessed--and men praise you when you prosper--
19Ps 49:19 he will join the generation of his fathers, who will never see the light of life.
19Ps 49:20 A man who has riches without understanding is like the beasts that perish.
19Ps 50:1 A psalm of Asaph. The Mighty One, God, the LORD, speaks and summons the earth from the rising of the sun to the place where it sets.
19Ps 50:2 From Zion, perfect in beauty, God shines forth.
19Ps 50:3 Our God comes and will not be silent; a fire devours before him, and around him a tempest rages.
19Ps 50:4 He summons the heavens above, and the earth, that he may judge his people£º
19Ps 50:5 "Gather to me my consecrated ones, who made a covenant with me by sacrifice."
19Ps 50:6 And the heavens proclaim his righteousness, for God himself is judge. Selah
19Ps 50:7 "Hear, O my people, and I will speak, O Israel, and I will testify against you£º I am God, your God.
19Ps 50:8 I do not rebuke you for your sacrifices or your burnt offerings, which are ever before me.
19Ps 50:9 I have no need of a bull from your stall or of goats from your pens,
19Ps 50:10 for every animal of the forest is mine, and the cattle on a thousand hills.
19Ps 50:11 I know every bird in the mountains, and the creatures of the field are mine.
19Ps 50:12 If I were hungry I would not tell you, for the world is mine, and all that is in it.
19Ps 50:13 Do I eat the flesh of bulls or drink the blood of goats?
19Ps 50:14 Sacrifice thank offerings to God, fulfill your vows to the Most High,
19Ps 50:15 and call upon me in the day of trouble; I will deliver you, and you will honor me."
19Ps 50:16 But to the wicked, God says£º "What right have you to recite my laws or take my covenant on your lips?
19Ps 50:17 You hate my instruction and cast my words behind you.
19Ps 50:18 When you see a thief, you join with him; you throw in your lot with adulterers.
19Ps 50:19 You use your mouth for evil and harness your tongue to deceit.
19Ps 50:20 You speak continually against your brother and slander your own mother's son.
19Ps 50:21 These things you have done and I kept silent; you thought I was altogether like you. But I will rebuke you and accuse you to your face.
19Ps 50:22 "Consider this, you who forget God, or I will tear you to pieces, with none to rescue£º
19Ps 50:23 He who sacrifices thank offerings honors me, and he prepares the way so that I may show him the salvation of God."
19Ps 51:1 For the director of music. A psalm of David. When the prophet Nathan came to him after David had committed adultery with Bathsheba. Have mercy on me, O God, according to your unfailing love; according to your great compassion blot out my transgressions.
19Ps 51:2 Wash away all my iniquity and cleanse me from my sin.
19Ps 51:3 For I know my transgressions, and my sin is always before me.
19Ps 51:4 Against you, you only, have I sinned and done what is evil in your sight, so that you are proved right when you speak and justified when you judge.
19Ps 51:5 Surely I was sinful at birth, sinful from the time my mother conceived me.
19Ps 51:6 Surely you desire truth in the inner parts; you teach me wisdom in the inmost place.
19Ps 51:7 Cleanse me with hyssop, and I will be clean; wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.
19Ps 51:8 Let me hear joy and gladness; let the bones you have crushed rejoice.
19Ps 51:9 Hide your face from my sins and blot out all my iniquity.
19Ps 51:10 Create in me a pure heart, O God, and renew a steadfast spirit within me.
19Ps 51:11 Do not cast me from your presence or take your Holy Spirit from me.
19Ps 51:12 Restore to me the joy of your salvation and grant me a willing spirit, to sustain me.
19Ps 51:13 Then I will teach transgressors your ways, and sinners will turn back to you.
19Ps 51:14 Save me from bloodguilt, O God, the God who saves me, and my tongue will sing of your righteousness.
19Ps 51:15 O Lord, open my lips, and my mouth will declare your praise.
19Ps 51:16 You do not delight in sacrifice, or I would bring it; you do not take pleasure in burnt offerings.
19Ps 51:17 The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit; a broken and contrite heart, O God, you will not despise.
19Ps 51:18 In your good pleasure make Zion prosper; build up the walls of Jerusalem.
19Ps 51:19 Then there will be righteous sacrifices, whole burnt offerings to delight you; then bulls will be offered on your altar.
19Ps 52:1 For the director of music. A maskil of David. When Doeg the Edomite had gone to Saul and told him£º "David has gone to the house of Ahimelech." Why do you boast of evil, you mighty man? Why do you boast all day long, you who are a disgrace in the eyes of God?
19Ps 52:2 Your tongue plots destruction; it is like a sharpened razor, you who practice deceit.
19Ps 52:3 You love evil rather than good, falsehood rather than speaking the truth. Selah
19Ps 52:4 You love every harmful word, O you deceitful tongue!
19Ps 52:5 Surely God will bring you down to everlasting ruin£º He will snatch you up and tear you from your tent; he will uproot you from the land of the living. Selah
19Ps 52:6 The righteous will see and fear; they will laugh at him, saying,
19Ps 52:7 "Here now is the man who did not make God his stronghold but trusted in his great wealth and grew strong by destroying others!"
19Ps 52:8 But I am like an olive tree flourishing in the house of God; I trust in God's unfailing love for ever and ever.
19Ps 52:9 I will praise you forever for what you have done; in your name I will hope, for your name is good. I will praise you in the presence of your saints.
19Ps 53:1 For the director of music. According to mahalath. A maskil of David. The fool says in his heart, "There is no God." They are corrupt, and their ways are vile; there is no one who does good.
19Ps 53:2 God looks down from heaven on the sons of men to see if there are any who understand, any who seek God.
19Ps 53:3 Everyone has turned away, they have together become corrupt; there is no one who does good, not even one.
19Ps 53:4 Will the evildoers never learn--those who devour my people as men eat bread and who do not call on God?
19Ps 53:5 There they were, overwhelmed with dread, where there was nothing to dread. God scattered the bones of those who attacked you; you put them to shame, for God despised them.
19Ps 53:6 Oh, that salvation for Israel would come out of Zion! When God restores the fortunes of his people, let Jacob rejoice and Israel be glad!
19Ps 54:1 For the director of music. With stringed instruments. A maskil of David. When the Ziphites had gone to Saul and said, "Is not David hiding among us?" Save me, O God, by your name; vindicate me by your might.
19Ps 54:2 Hear my prayer, O God; listen to the words of my mouth.
19Ps 54:3 Strangers are attacking me; ruthless men seek my life--men without regard for God. Selah
19Ps 54:4 Surely God is my help; the Lord is the one who sustains me.
19Ps 54:5 Let evil recoil on those who slander me; in your faithfulness destroy them.
19Ps 54:6 I will sacrifice a freewill offering to you; I will praise your name, O LORD, for it is good.
19Ps 54:7 For he has delivered me from all my troubles, and my eyes have looked in triumph on my foes.
19Ps 55:1 For the director of music. With stringed instruments. A maskil of David. Listen to my prayer, O God, do not ignore my plea;
19Ps 55:2 hear me and answer me. My thoughts trouble me and I am distraught
19Ps 55:3 at the voice of the enemy, at the stares of the wicked; for they bring down suffering upon me and revile me in their anger.
19Ps 55:4 My heart is in anguish within me; the terrors of death assail me.
19Ps 55:5 Fear and trembling have beset me; horror has overwhelmed me.
19Ps 55:6 I said, "Oh, that I had the wings of a dove! I would fly away and be at rest--
19Ps 55:7 I would flee far away and stay in the desert; Selah
19Ps 55:8 I would hurry to my place of shelter, far from the tempest and storm."
19Ps 55:9 Confuse the wicked, O Lord, confound their speech, for I see violence and strife in the city.
19Ps 55:10 Day and night they prowl about on its walls; malice and abuse are within it.
19Ps 55:11 Destructive forces are at work in the city; threats and lies never leave its streets.
19Ps 55:12 If an enemy were insulting me, I could endure it; if a foe were raising himself against me, I could hide from him.
19Ps 55:13 But it is you, a man like myself, my companion, my close friend,
19Ps 55:14 with whom I once enjoyed sweet fellowship as we walked with the throng at the house of God.
19Ps 55:15 Let death take my enemies by surprise; let them go down alive to the grave, for evil finds lodging among them.
19Ps 55:16 But I call to God, and the LORD saves me.
19Ps 55:17 Evening, morning and noon I cry out in distress, and he hears my voice.
19Ps 55:18 He ransoms me unharmed from the battle waged against me, even though many oppose me.
19Ps 55:19 God, who is enthroned forever, will hear them and afflict them--Selah men who never change their ways and have no fear of God.
19Ps 55:20 My companion attacks his friends; he violates his covenant.
19Ps 55:21 His speech is smooth as butter, yet war is in his heart; his words are more soothing than oil, yet they are drawn swords.
19Ps 55:22 Cast your cares on the LORD and he will sustain you; he will never let the righteous fall.
19Ps 55:23 But you, O God, will bring down the wicked into the pit of corruption; bloodthirsty and deceitful men will not live out half their days. But as for me, I trust in you.
19Ps 56:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"A Dove on Distant Oaks." Of David. A miktam. When the Philistines had seized him in Gath. Be merciful to me, O God, for men hotly pursue me; all day long they press their attack.
19Ps 56:2 My slanderers pursue me all day long; many are attacking me in their pride.
19Ps 56:3 When I am afraid, I will trust in you.
19Ps 56:4 In God, whose word I praise, in God I trust; I will not be afraid. What can mortal man do to me?
19Ps 56:5 All day long they twist my words; they are always plotting to harm me.
19Ps 56:6 They conspire, they lurk, they watch my steps, eager to take my life.
19Ps 56:7 On no account let them escape; in your anger, O God, bring down the nations.
19Ps 56:8 Record my lament; list my tears on your scroll--are they not in your record?
19Ps 56:9 Then my enemies will turn back when I call for help. By this I will know that God is for me.
19Ps 56:10 In God, whose word I praise, in the LORD, whose word I praise--
19Ps 56:11 in God I trust; I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?
19Ps 56:12 I am under vows to you, O God; I will present my thank offerings to you.
19Ps 56:13 For you have delivered me from death and my feet from stumbling, that I may walk before God in the light of life.
19Ps 57:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"Do Not Destroy." Of David. A miktam. When he had fled from Saul into the cave. Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy on me, for in you my soul takes refuge. I will take refuge in the shadow of your wings until the disaster has passed.
19Ps 57:2 I cry out to God Most High, to God, who fulfills his purpose for me.
19Ps 57:3 He sends from heaven and saves me, rebuking those who hotly pursue me; Selah God sends his love and his faithfulness.
19Ps 57:4 I am in the midst of lions; I lie among ravenous beasts--men whose teeth are spears and arrows, whose tongues are sharp swords.
19Ps 57:5 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens; let your glory be over all the earth.
19Ps 57:6 They spread a net for my feet--I was bowed down in distress. They dug a pit in my path--but they have fallen into it themselves. Selah
19Ps 57:7 My heart is steadfast, O God, my heart is steadfast; I will sing and make music.
19Ps 57:8 Awake, my soul! Awake, harp and lyre! I will awaken the dawn.
19Ps 57:9 I will praise you, O Lord, among the nations; I will sing of you among the peoples.
19Ps 57:10 For great is your love, reaching to the heavens; your faithfulness reaches to the skies.
19Ps 57:11 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens; let your glory be over all the earth.
19Ps 58:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"Do Not Destroy." Of David. A miktam. Do you rulers indeed speak justly? Do you judge uprightly among men?
19Ps 58:2 No, in your heart you devise injustice, and your hands mete out violence on the earth.
19Ps 58:3 Even from birth the wicked go astray; from the womb they are wayward and speak lies.
19Ps 58:4 Their venom is like the venom of a snake, like that of a cobra that has stopped its ears,
19Ps 58:5 that will not heed the tune of the charmer, however skillful the enchanter may be.
19Ps 58:6 Break the teeth in their mouths, O God; tear out, O LORD, the fangs of the lions!
19Ps 58:7 Let them vanish like water that flows away; when they draw the bow, let their arrows be blunted.
19Ps 58:8 Like a slug melting away as it moves along, like a stillborn child, may they not see the sun.
19Ps 58:9 Before your pots can feel the heat of the thorns--whether they be green or dry--the wicked will be swept away.
19Ps 58:10 The righteous will be glad when they are avenged, when they bathe their feet in the blood of the wicked.
19Ps 58:11 Then men will say, "Surely the righteous still are rewarded; surely there is a God who judges the earth."
19Ps 59:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"Do Not Destroy." Of David. A miktam. When Saul had sent men to watch David's house in order to kill him. Deliver me from my enemies, O God; protect me from those who rise up against me.
19Ps 59:2 Deliver me from evildoers and save me from bloodthirsty men.
19Ps 59:3 See how they lie in wait for me! Fierce men conspire against me for no offense or sin of mine, O LORD.
19Ps 59:4 I have done no wrong, yet they are ready to attack me. Arise to help me; look on my plight!
19Ps 59:5 O LORD God Almighty, the God of Israel, rouse yourself to punish all the nations; show no mercy to wicked traitors. Selah
19Ps 59:6 They return at evening, snarling like dogs, and prowl about the city.
19Ps 59:7 See what they spew from their mouths--they spew out swords from their lips, and they say, "Who can hear us?"
19Ps 59:8 But you, O LORD, laugh at them; you scoff at all those nations.
19Ps 59:9 O my Strength, I watch for you; you, O God, are my fortress,
19Ps 59:10 my loving God. God will go before me and will let me gloat over those who slander me.
19Ps 59:11 But do not kill them, O Lord our shield, or my people will forget. In your might make them wander about, and bring them down.
19Ps 59:12 For the sins of their mouths, for the words of their lips, let them be caught in their pride. For the curses and lies they utter,
19Ps 59:13 consume them in wrath, consume them till they are no more. Then it will be known to the ends of the earth that God rules over Jacob. Selah
19Ps 59:14 They return at evening, snarling like dogs, and prowl about the city.
19Ps 59:15 They wander about for food and howl if not satisfied.
19Ps 59:16 But I will sing of your strength, in the morning I will sing of your love; for you are my fortress, my refuge in times of trouble.
19Ps 59:17 O my Strength, I sing praise to you; you, O God, are my fortress, my loving God.
19Ps 60:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"The Lily of the Covenant." A miktam of David. For teaching. When he fought Aram Naharaim and Aram Zobah, and when Joab returned and struck down twelve thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt. You have rejected us, O God, and burst forth upon us; you have been angry--now restore us!
19Ps 60:2 You have shaken the land and torn it open; mend its fractures, for it is quaking.
19Ps 60:3 You have shown your people desperate times; you have given us wine that makes us stagger.
19Ps 60:4 But for those who fear you, you have raised a banner to be unfurled against the bow. Selah
19Ps 60:5 Save us and help us with your right hand, that those you love may be delivered.
19Ps 60:6 God has spoken from his sanctuary£º "In triumph I will parcel out Shechem and measure off the Valley of Succoth.
19Ps 60:7 Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim is my helmet, Judah my scepter.
19Ps 60:8 Moab is my washbasin, upon Edom I toss my sandal; over Philistia I shout in triumph."
19Ps 60:9 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?
19Ps 60:10 Is it not you, O God, you who have rejected us and no longer go out with our armies?
19Ps 60:11 Give us aid against the enemy, for the help of man is worthless.
19Ps 60:12 With God we will gain the victory, and he will trample down our enemies.
19Ps 61:1 For the director of music. With stringed instruments. Of David. Hear my cry, O God; listen to my prayer.
19Ps 61:2 From the ends of the earth I call to you, I call as my heart grows faint; lead me to the rock that is higher than I.
19Ps 61:3 For you have been my refuge, a strong tower against the foe.
19Ps 61:4 I long to dwell in your tent forever and take refuge in the shelter of your wings. Selah
19Ps 61:5 For you have heard my vows, O God; you have given me the heritage of those who fear your name.
19Ps 61:6 Increase the days of the king's life, his years for many generations.
19Ps 61:7 May he be enthroned in God's presence forever; appoint your love and faithfulness to protect him.
19Ps 61:8 Then will I ever sing praise to your name and fulfill my vows day after day.
19Ps 62:1 For the director of music. For Jeduthun. A psalm of David. My soul finds rest in God alone; my salvation comes from him.
19Ps 62:2 He alone is my rock and my salvation; he is my fortress, I will never be shaken.
19Ps 62:3 How long will you assault a man? Would all of you throw him down--this leaning wall, this tottering fence?
19Ps 62:4 They fully intend to topple him from his lofty place; they take delight in lies. With their mouths they bless, but in their hearts they curse. Selah
19Ps 62:5 Find rest, O my soul, in God alone; my hope comes from him.
19Ps 62:6 He alone is my rock and my salvation; he is my fortress, I will not be shaken.
19Ps 62:7 My salvation and my honor depend on God; he is my mighty rock, my refuge.
19Ps 62:8 Trust in him at all times, O people; pour out your hearts to him, for God is our refuge. Selah
19Ps 62:9 Lowborn men are but a breath, the highborn are but a lie; if weighed on a balance, they are nothing; together they are only a breath.
19Ps 62:10 Do not trust in extortion or take pride in stolen goods; though your riches increase, do not set your heart on them.
19Ps 62:11 One thing God has spoken, two things have I heard£º that you, O God, are strong,
19Ps 62:12 and that you, O Lord, are loving. Surely you will reward each person according to what he has done.
19Ps 63:1 A psalm of David. When he was in the Desert of Judah. O God, you are my God, earnestly I seek you; my soul thirsts for you, my body longs for you, in a dry and weary land where there is no water.
19Ps 63:2 I have seen you in the sanctuary and beheld your power and your glory.
19Ps 63:3 Because your love is better than life, my lips will glorify you.
19Ps 63:4 I will praise you as long as I live, and in your name I will lift up my hands.
19Ps 63:5 My soul will be satisfied as with the richest of foods; with singing lips my mouth will praise you.
19Ps 63:6 On my bed I remember you; I think of you through the watches of the night.
19Ps 63:7 Because you are my help, I sing in the shadow of your wings.
19Ps 63:8 My soul clings to you; your right hand upholds me.
19Ps 63:9 They who seek my life will be destroyed; they will go down to the depths of the earth.
19Ps 63:10 They will be given over to the sword and become food for jackals.
19Ps 63:11 But the king will rejoice in God; all who swear by God's name will praise him, while the mouths of liars will be silenced.
19Ps 64:1 For the director of music. A psalm of David. Hear me, O God, as I voice my complaint; protect my life from the threat of the enemy.
19Ps 64:2 Hide me from the conspiracy of the wicked, from that noisy crowd of evildoers.
19Ps 64:3 They sharpen their tongues like swords and aim their words like deadly arrows.
19Ps 64:4 They shoot from ambush at the innocent man; they shoot at him suddenly, without fear.
19Ps 64:5 They encourage each other in evil plans, they talk about hiding their snares; they say, "Who will see them?"
19Ps 64:6 They plot injustice and say, "We have devised a perfect plan!" Surely the mind and heart of man are cunning.
19Ps 64:7 But God will shoot them with arrows; suddenly they will be struck down.
19Ps 64:8 He will turn their own tongues against them and bring them to ruin; all who see them will shake their heads in scorn.
19Ps 64:9 All mankind will fear; they will proclaim the works of God and ponder what he has done.
19Ps 64:10 Let the righteous rejoice in the LORD and take refuge in him; let all the upright in heart praise him!
19Ps 65:1 For the director of music. A psalm of David. A song. Praise awaits you, O God, in Zion; to you our vows will be fulfilled.
19Ps 65:2 O you who hear prayer, to you all men will come.
19Ps 65:3 When we were overwhelmed by sins, you forgave our transgressions.
19Ps 65:4 Blessed are those you choose and bring near to live in your courts! We are filled with the good things of your house, of your holy temple.
19Ps 65:5 You answer us with awesome deeds of righteousness, O God our Savior, the hope of all the ends of the earth and of the farthest seas,
19Ps 65:6 who formed the mountains by your power, having armed yourself with strength,
19Ps 65:7 who stilled the roaring of the seas, the roaring of their waves, and the turmoil of the nations.
19Ps 65:8 Those living far away fear your wonders; where morning dawns and evening fades you call forth songs of joy.
19Ps 65:9 You care for the land and water it; you enrich it abundantly. The streams of God are filled with water to provide the people with grain, for so you have ordained it.
19Ps 65:10 You drench its furrows and level its ridges; you soften it with showers and bless its crops.
19Ps 65:11 You crown the year with your bounty, and your carts overflow with abundance.
19Ps 65:12 The grasslands of the desert overflow; the hills are clothed with gladness.
19Ps 65:13 The meadows are covered with flocks and the valleys are mantled with grain; they shout for joy and sing.
19Ps 66:1 For the director of music. A song. A psalm. Shout with joy to God, all the earth!
19Ps 66:2 Sing the glory of his name; make his praise glorious!
19Ps 66:3 Say to God, "How awesome are your deeds! So great is your power that your enemies cringe before you.
19Ps 66:4 All the earth bows down to you; they sing praise to you, they sing praise to your name." Selah
19Ps 66:5 Come and see what God has done, how awesome his works in man's behalf!
19Ps 66:6 He turned the sea into dry land, they passed through the waters on foot--come, let us rejoice in him.
19Ps 66:7 He rules forever by his power, his eyes watch the nations--let not the rebellious rise up against him. Selah
19Ps 66:8 Praise our God, O peoples, let the sound of his praise be heard;
19Ps 66:9 he has preserved our lives and kept our feet from slipping.
19Ps 66:10 For you, O God, tested us; you refined us like silver.
19Ps 66:11 You brought us into prison and laid burdens on our backs.
19Ps 66:12 You let men ride over our heads; we went through fire and water, but you brought us to a place of abundance.
19Ps 66:13 I will come to your temple with burnt offerings and fulfill my vows to you--
19Ps 66:14 vows my lips promised and my mouth spoke when I was in trouble.
19Ps 66:15 I will sacrifice fat animals to you and an offering of rams; I will offer bulls and goats. Selah
19Ps 66:16 Come and listen, all you who fear God; let me tell you what he has done for me.
19Ps 66:17 I cried out to him with my mouth; his praise was on my tongue.
19Ps 66:18 If I had cherished sin in my heart, the Lord would not have listened;
19Ps 66:19 but God has surely listened and heard my voice in prayer.
19Ps 66:20 Praise be to God, who has not rejected my prayer or withheld his love from me!
19Ps 67:1 For the director of music. With stringed instruments. A psalm. A song. May God be gracious to us and bless us and make his face shine upon us, Selah
19Ps 67:2 that your ways may be known on earth, your salvation among all nations.
19Ps 67:3 May the peoples praise you, O God; may all the peoples praise you.
19Ps 67:4 May the nations be glad and sing for joy, for you rule the peoples justly and guide the nations of the earth. Selah
19Ps 67:5 May the peoples praise you, O God; may all the peoples praise you.
19Ps 67:6 Then the land will yield its harvest, and God, our God, will bless us.
19Ps 67:7 God will bless us, and all the ends of the earth will fear him.
19Ps 68:1 For the director of music. Of David. A psalm. A song. May God arise, may his enemies be scattered; may his foes flee before him.
19Ps 68:2 As smoke is blown away by the wind, may you blow them away; as wax melts before the fire, may the wicked perish before God.
19Ps 68:3 But may the righteous be glad and rejoice before God; may they be happy and joyful.
19Ps 68:4 Sing to God, sing praise to his name, extol him who rides on the clouds--his name is the LORD--and rejoice before him.
19Ps 68:5 A father to the fatherless, a defender of widows, is God in his holy dwelling.
19Ps 68:6 God sets the lonely in families, he leads forth the prisoners with singing; but the rebellious live in a sun-scorched land.
19Ps 68:7 When you went out before your people, O God, when you marched through the wasteland, Selah
19Ps 68:8 the earth shook, the heavens poured down rain, before God, the One of Sinai, before God, the God of Israel.
19Ps 68:9 You gave abundant showers, O God; you refreshed your weary inheritance.
19Ps 68:10 Your people settled in it, and from your bounty, O God, you provided for the poor.
19Ps 68:11 The Lord announced the word, and great was the company of those who proclaimed it£º
19Ps 68:12 "Kings and armies flee in haste; in the camps men divide the plunder.
19Ps 68:13 Even while you sleep among the campfires, the wings of my dove are sheathed with silver, its feathers with shining gold."
19Ps 68:14 When the Almighty scattered the kings in the land, it was like snow fallen on Zalmon.
19Ps 68:15 The mountains of Bashan are majestic mountains; rugged are the mountains of Bashan.
19Ps 68:16 Why gaze in envy, O rugged mountains, at the mountain where God chooses to reign, where the LORD himself will dwell forever?
19Ps 68:17 The chariots of God are tens of thousands and thousands of thousands; the Lord has come from Sinai into his sanctuary.
19Ps 68:18 When you ascended on high, you led captives in your train; you received gifts from men, even from the rebellious--that you, O LORD God, might dwell there.
19Ps 68:19 Praise be to the Lord, to God our Savior, who daily bears our burdens. Selah
19Ps 68:20 Our God is a God who saves; from the Sovereign LORD comes escape from death.
19Ps 68:21 Surely God will crush the heads of his enemies, the hairy crowns of those who go on in their sins.
19Ps 68:22 The Lord says, "I will bring them from Bashan; I will bring them from the depths of the sea,
19Ps 68:23 that you may plunge your feet in the blood of your foes, while the tongues of your dogs have their share."
19Ps 68:24 Your procession has come into view, O God, the procession of my God and King into the sanctuary.
19Ps 68:25 In front are the singers, after them the musicians; with them are the maidens playing tambourines.
19Ps 68:26 Praise God in the great congregation; praise the LORD in the assembly of Israel.
19Ps 68:27 There is the little tribe of Benjamin, leading them, there the great throng of Judah's princes, and there the princes of Zebulun and of Naphtali.
19Ps 68:28 Summon your power, O God; show us your strength, O God, as you have done before.
19Ps 68:29 Because of your temple at Jerusalem kings will bring you gifts.
19Ps 68:30 Rebuke the beast among the reeds, the herd of bulls among the calves of the nations. Humbled, may it bring bars of silver. Scatter the nations who delight in war.
19Ps 68:31 Envoys will come from Egypt; Cush will submit herself to God.
19Ps 68:32 Sing to God, O kingdoms of the earth, sing praise to the Lord, Selah
19Ps 68:33 to him who rides the ancient skies above, who thunders with mighty voice.
19Ps 68:34 Proclaim the power of God, whose majesty is over Israel, whose power is in the skies.
19Ps 68:35 You are awesome, O God, in your sanctuary; the God of Israel gives power and strength to his people. Praise be to God!
19Ps 69:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"Lilies." Of David. Save me, O God, for the waters have come up to my neck.
19Ps 69:2 I sink in the miry depths, where there is no foothold. I have come into the deep waters; the floods engulf me.
19Ps 69:3 I am worn out calling for help; my throat is parched. My eyes fail, looking for my God.
19Ps 69:4 Those who hate me without reason outnumber the hairs of my head; many are my enemies without cause, those who seek to destroy me. I am forced to restore what I did not steal.
19Ps 69:5 You know my folly, O God; my guilt is not hidden from you.
19Ps 69:6 May those who hope in you not be disgraced because of me, O Lord, the LORD Almighty; may those who seek you not be put to shame because of me, O God of Israel.
19Ps 69:7 For I endure scorn for your sake, and shame covers my face.
19Ps 69:8 I am a stranger to my brothers, an alien to my own mother's sons;
19Ps 69:9 for zeal for your house consumes me, and the insults of those who insult you fall on me.
19Ps 69:10 When I weep and fast, I must endure scorn;
19Ps 69:11 when I put on sackcloth, people make sport of me.
19Ps 69:12 Those who sit at the gate mock me, and I am the song of the drunkards.
19Ps 69:13 But I pray to you, O LORD, in the time of your favor; in your great love, O God, answer me with your sure salvation.
19Ps 69:14 Rescue me from the mire, do not let me sink; deliver me from those who hate me, from the deep waters.
19Ps 69:15 Do not let the floodwaters engulf me or the depths swallow me up or the pit close its mouth over me.
19Ps 69:16 Answer me, O LORD, out of the goodness of your love; in your great mercy turn to me.
19Ps 69:17 Do not hide your face from your servant; answer me quickly, for I am in trouble.
19Ps 69:18 Come near and rescue me; redeem me because of my foes.
19Ps 69:19 You know how I am scorned, disgraced and shamed; all my enemies are before you.
19Ps 69:20 Scorn has broken my heart and has left me helpless; I looked for sympathy, but there was none, for comforters, but I found none.
19Ps 69:21 They put gall in my food and gave me vinegar for my thirst.
19Ps 69:22 May the table set before them become a snare; may it become retribution and a trap.
19Ps 69:23 May their eyes be darkened so they cannot see, and their backs be bent forever.
19Ps 69:24 Pour out your wrath on them; let your fierce anger overtake them.
19Ps 69:25 May their place be deserted; let there be no one to dwell in their tents.
19Ps 69:26 For they persecute those you wound and talk about the pain of those you hurt.
19Ps 69:27 Charge them with crime upon crime; do not let them share in your salvation.
19Ps 69:28 May they be blotted out of the book of life and not be listed with the righteous.
19Ps 69:29 I am in pain and distress; may your salvation, O God, protect me.
19Ps 69:30 I will praise God's name in song and glorify him with thanksgiving.
19Ps 69:31 This will please the LORD more than an ox, more than a bull with its horns and hoofs.
19Ps 69:32 The poor will see and be glad--you who seek God, may your hearts live!
19Ps 69:33 The LORD hears the needy and does not despise his captive people.
19Ps 69:34 Let heaven and earth praise him, the seas and all that move in them,
19Ps 69:35 for God will save Zion and rebuild the cities of Judah. Then people will settle there and possess it;
19Ps 69:36 the children of his servants will inherit it, and those who love his name will dwell there.
19Ps 70:1 For the director of music. Of David. A petition. Hasten, O God, to save me; O LORD, come quickly to help me.
19Ps 70:2 May those who seek my life be put to shame and confusion; may all who desire my ruin be turned back in disgrace.
19Ps 70:3 May those who say to me, "Aha! Aha!" turn back because of their shame.
19Ps 70:4 But may all who seek you rejoice and be glad in you; may those who love your salvation always say, "Let God be exalted!"
19Ps 70:5 Yet I am poor and needy; come quickly to me, O God. You are my help and my deliverer; O LORD, do not delay.
19Ps 71:1 In you, O LORD, I have taken refuge; let me never be put to shame.
19Ps 71:2 Rescue me and deliver me in your righteousness; turn your ear to me and save me.
19Ps 71:3 Be my rock of refuge, to which I can always go; give the command to save me, for you are my rock and my fortress.
19Ps 71:4 Deliver me, O my God, from the hand of the wicked, from the grasp of evil and cruel men.
19Ps 71:5 For you have been my hope, O Sovereign LORD, my confidence since my youth.
19Ps 71:6 From birth I have relied on you; you brought me forth from my mother's womb. I will ever praise you.
19Ps 71:7 I have become like a portent to many, but you are my strong refuge.
19Ps 71:8 My mouth is filled with your praise, declaring your splendor all day long.
19Ps 71:9 Do not cast me away when I am old; do not forsake me when my strength is gone.
19Ps 71:10 For my enemies speak against me; those who wait to kill me conspire together.
19Ps 71:11 They say, "God has forsaken him; pursue him and seize him, for no one will rescue him."
19Ps 71:12 Be not far from me, O God; come quickly, O my God, to help me.
19Ps 71:13 May my accusers perish in shame; may those who want to harm me be covered with scorn and disgrace.
19Ps 71:14 But as for me, I will always have hope; I will praise you more and more.
19Ps 71:15 My mouth will tell of your righteousness, of your salvation all day long, though I know not its measure.
19Ps 71:16 I will come and proclaim your mighty acts, O Sovereign LORD; I will proclaim your righteousness, yours alone.
19Ps 71:17 Since my youth, O God, you have taught me, and to this day I declare your marvelous deeds.
19Ps 71:18 Even when I am old and gray, do not forsake me, O God, till I declare your power to the next generation, your might to all who are to come.
19Ps 71:19 Your righteousness reaches to the skies, O God, you who have done great things. Who, O God, is like you?
19Ps 71:20 Though you have made me see troubles, many and bitter, you will restore my life again; from the depths of the earth you will again bring me up.
19Ps 71:21 You will increase my honor and comfort me once again.
19Ps 71:22 I will praise you with the harp for your faithfulness, O my God; I will sing praise to you with the lyre, O Holy One of Israel.
19Ps 71:23 My lips will shout for joy when I sing praise to you--I, whom you have redeemed.
19Ps 71:24 My tongue will tell of your righteous acts all day long, for those who wanted to harm me have been put to shame and confusion.
19Ps 72:1 Of Solomon. Endow the king with your justice, O God, the royal son with your righteousness.
19Ps 72:2 He will judge your people in righteousness, your afflicted ones with justice.
19Ps 72:3 The mountains will bring prosperity to the people, the hills the fruit of righteousness.
19Ps 72:4 He will defend the afflicted among the people and save the children of the needy; he will crush the oppressor.
19Ps 72:5 He will endure as long as the sun, as long as the moon, through all generations.
19Ps 72:6 He will be like rain falling on a mown field, like showers watering the earth.
19Ps 72:7 In his days the righteous will flourish; prosperity will abound till the moon is no more.
19Ps 72:8 He will rule from sea to sea and from the River to the ends of the earth.
19Ps 72:9 The desert tribes will bow before him and his enemies will lick the dust.
19Ps 72:10 The kings of Tarshish and of distant shores will bring tribute to him; the kings of Sheba and Seba will present him gifts.
19Ps 72:11 All kings will bow down to him and all nations will serve him.
19Ps 72:12 For he will deliver the needy who cry out, the afflicted who have no one to help.
19Ps 72:13 He will take pity on the weak and the needy and save the needy from death.
19Ps 72:14 He will rescue them from oppression and violence, for precious is their blood in his sight.
19Ps 72:15 Long may he live! May gold from Sheba be given him. May people ever pray for him and bless him all day long.
19Ps 72:16 Let grain abound throughout the land; on the tops of the hills may it sway. Let its fruit flourish like Lebanon; let it thrive like the grass of the field.
19Ps 72:17 May his name endure forever; may it continue as long as the sun. All nations will be blessed through him, and they will call him blessed.
19Ps 72:18 Praise be to the LORD God, the God of Israel, who alone does marvelous deeds.
19Ps 72:19 Praise be to his glorious name forever; may the whole earth be filled with his glory. Amen and Amen.
19Ps 72:20 This concludes the prayers of David son of Jesse.
19Ps 73:1 A psalm of Asaph. Surely God is good to Israel, to those who are pure in heart.
19Ps 73:2 But as for me, my feet had almost slipped; I had nearly lost my foothold.
19Ps 73:3 For I envied the arrogant when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
19Ps 73:4 They have no struggles; their bodies are healthy and strong.
19Ps 73:5 They are free from the burdens common to man; they are not plagued by human ills.
19Ps 73:6 Therefore pride is their necklace; they clothe themselves with violence.
19Ps 73:7 From their callous hearts comes iniquity; the evil conceits of their minds know no limits.
19Ps 73:8 They scoff, and speak with malice; in their arrogance they threaten oppression.
19Ps 73:9 Their mouths lay claim to heaven, and their tongues take possession of the earth.
19Ps 73:10 Therefore their people turn to them and drink up waters in abundance.
19Ps 73:11 They say, "How can God know? Does the Most High have knowledge?"
19Ps 73:12 This is what the wicked are like--always carefree, they increase in wealth.
19Ps 73:13 Surely in vain have I kept my heart pure; in vain have I washed my hands in innocence.
19Ps 73:14 All day long I have been plagued; I have been punished every morning.
19Ps 73:15 If I had said, "I will speak thus," I would have betrayed your children.
19Ps 73:16 When I tried to understand all this, it was oppressive to me
19Ps 73:17 till I entered the sanctuary of God; then I understood their final destiny.
19Ps 73:18 Surely you place them on slippery ground; you cast them down to ruin.
19Ps 73:19 How suddenly are they destroyed, completely swept away by terrors!
19Ps 73:20 As a dream when one awakes, so when you arise, O Lord, you will despise them as fantasies.
19Ps 73:21 When my heart was grieved and my spirit embittered,
19Ps 73:22 I was senseless and ignorant; I was a brute beast before you.
19Ps 73:23 Yet I am always with you; you hold me by my right hand.
19Ps 73:24 You guide me with your counsel, and afterward you will take me into glory.
19Ps 73:25 Whom have I in heaven but you? And earth has nothing I desire besides you.
19Ps 73:26 My flesh and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.
19Ps 73:27 Those who are far from you will perish; you destroy all who are unfaithful to you.
19Ps 73:28 But as for me, it is good to be near God. I have made the Sovereign LORD my refuge; I will tell of all your deeds.
19Ps 74:1 A maskil of Asaph. Why have you rejected us forever, O God? Why does your anger smolder against the sheep of your pasture?
19Ps 74:2 Remember the people you purchased of old, the tribe of your inheritance, whom you redeemed--Mount Zion, where you dwelt.
19Ps 74:3 Turn your steps toward these everlasting ruins, all this destruction the enemy has brought on the sanctuary.
19Ps 74:4 Your foes roared in the place where you met with us; they set up their standards as signs.
19Ps 74:5 They behaved like men wielding axes to cut through a thicket of trees.
19Ps 74:6 They smashed all the carved paneling with their axes and hatchets.
19Ps 74:7 They burned your sanctuary to the ground; they defiled the dwelling place of your Name.
19Ps 74:8 They said in their hearts, "We will crush them completely!" They burned every place where God was worshiped in the land.
19Ps 74:9 We are given no miraculous signs; no prophets are left, and none of us knows how long this will be.
19Ps 74:10 How long will the enemy mock you, O God? Will the foe revile your name forever?
19Ps 74:11 Why do you hold back your hand, your right hand? Take it from the folds of your garment and destroy them!
19Ps 74:12 But you, O God, are my king from of old; you bring salvation upon the earth.
19Ps 74:13 It was you who split open the sea by your power; you broke the heads of the monster in the waters.
19Ps 74:14 It was you who crushed the heads of Leviathan and gave him as food to the creatures of the desert.
19Ps 74:15 It was you who opened up springs and streams; you dried up the ever flowing rivers.
19Ps 74:16 The day is yours, and yours also the night; you established the sun and moon.
19Ps 74:17 It was you who set all the boundaries of the earth; you made both summer and winter.
19Ps 74:18 Remember how the enemy has mocked you, O LORD, how foolish people have reviled your name.
19Ps 74:19 Do not hand over the life of your dove to wild beasts; do not forget the lives of your afflicted people forever.
19Ps 74:20 Have regard for your covenant, because haunts of violence fill the dark places of the land.
19Ps 74:21 Do not let the oppressed retreat in disgrace; may the poor and needy praise your name.
19Ps 74:22 Rise up, O God, and defend your cause; remember how fools mock you all day long.
19Ps 74:23 Do not ignore the clamor of your adversaries, the uproar of your enemies, which rises continually.
19Ps 75:1 For the director of music. To the tune of"Do Not Destroy." A psalm of Asaph. A song. We give thanks to you, O God, we give thanks, for your Name is near; men tell of your wonderful deeds.
19Ps 75:2 You say, "I choose the appointed time; it is I who judge uprightly.
19Ps 75:3 When the earth and all its people quake, it is I who hold its pillars firm. Selah
19Ps 75:4 To the arrogant I say, 'Boast no more,' and to the wicked, 'Do not lift up your horns.
19Ps 75:5 Do not lift your horns against heaven; do not speak with outstretched neck.'"
19Ps 75:6 No one from the east or the west or from the desert can exalt a man.
19Ps 75:7 But it is God who judges£º He brings one down, he exalts another.
19Ps 75:8 In the hand of the LORD is a cup full of foaming wine mixed with spices; he pours it out, and all the wicked of the earth drink it down to its very dregs.
19Ps 75:9 As for me, I will declare this forever; I will sing praise to the God of Jacob.
19Ps 75:10 I will cut off the horns of all the wicked, but the horns of the righteous will be lifted up.
19Ps 76:1 For the director of music. With stringed instruments. A psalm of Asaph. A song. In Judah God is known; his name is great in Israel.
19Ps 76:2 His tent is in Salem, his dwelling place in Zion.
19Ps 76:3 There he broke the flashing arrows, the shields and the swords, the weapons of war. Selah
19Ps 76:4 You are resplendent with light, more majestic than mountains rich with game.
19Ps 76:5 Valiant men lie plundered, they sleep their last sleep; not one of the warriors can lift his hands.
19Ps 76:6 At your rebuke, O God of Jacob, both horse and chariot lie still.
19Ps 76:7 You alone are to be feared. Who can stand before you when you are angry?
19Ps 76:8 From heaven you pronounced judgment, and the land feared and was quiet--
19Ps 76:9 when you, O God, rose up to judge, to save all the afflicted of the land. Selah
19Ps 76:10 Surely your wrath against men brings you praise, and the survivors of your wrath are restrained.
19Ps 76:11 Make vows to the LORD your God and fulfill them; let all the neighboring lands bring gifts to the One to be feared.
19Ps 76:12 He breaks the spirit of rulers; he is feared by the kings of the earth.
19Ps 77:1 For the director of music. For Jeduthun. Of Asaph. A psalm. I cried out to God for help; I cried out to God to hear me.
19Ps 77:2 When I was in distress, I sought the Lord; at night I stretched out untiring hands and my soul refused to be comforted.
19Ps 77:3 I remembered you, O God, and I groaned; I mused, and my spirit grew faint. Selah
19Ps 77:4 You kept my eyes from closing; I was too troubled to speak.
19Ps 77:5 I thought about the former days, the years of long ago;
19Ps 77:6 I remembered my songs in the night. My heart mused and my spirit inquired£º
19Ps 77:7 "Will the Lord reject forever? Will he never show his favor again?
19Ps 77:8 Has his unfailing love vanished forever? Has his promise failed for all time?
19Ps 77:9 Has God forgotten to be merciful? Has he in anger withheld his compassion?" Selah
19Ps 77:10 Then I thought, "To this I will appeal£º the years of the right hand of the Most High."
19Ps 77:11 I will remember the deeds of the LORD; yes, I will remember your miracles of long ago.
19Ps 77:12 I will meditate on all your works and consider all your mighty deeds.
19Ps 77:13 Your ways, O God, are holy. What god is so great as our God?
19Ps 77:14 You are the God who performs miracles; you display your power among the peoples.
19Ps 77:15 With your mighty arm you redeemed your people, the descendants of Jacob and Joseph. Selah
19Ps 77:16 The waters saw you, O God, the waters saw you and writhed; the very depths were convulsed.
19Ps 77:17 The clouds poured down water, the skies resounded with thunder; your arrows flashed back and forth.
19Ps 77:18 Your thunder was heard in the whirlwind, your lightning lit up the world; the earth trembled and quaked.
19Ps 77:19 Your path led through the sea, your way through the mighty waters, though your footprints were not seen.
19Ps 77:20 You led your people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.
19Ps 78:1 A maskil of Asaph. O my people, hear my teaching; listen to the words of my mouth.
19Ps 78:2 I will open my mouth in parables, I will utter hidden things, things from of old--
19Ps 78:3 what we have heard and known, what our fathers have told us.
19Ps 78:4 We will not hide them from their children; we will tell the next generation the praiseworthy deeds of the LORD, his power, and the wonders he has done.
19Ps 78:5 He decreed statutes for Jacob and established the law in Israel, which he commanded our forefathers to teach their children,
19Ps 78:6 so the next generation would know them, even the children yet to be born, and they in turn would tell their children.
19Ps 78:7 Then they would put their trust in God and would not forget his deeds but would keep his commands.
19Ps 78:8 They would not be like their forefathers--a stubborn and rebellious generation, whose hearts were not loyal to God, whose spirits were not faithful to him.
19Ps 78:9 The men of Ephraim, though armed with bows, turned back on the day of battle;
19Ps 78:10 they did not keep God's covenant and refused to live by his law.
19Ps 78:11 They forgot what he had done, the wonders he had shown them.
19Ps 78:12 He did miracles in the sight of their fathers in the land of Egypt, in the region of Zoan.
19Ps 78:13 He divided the sea and led them through; he made the water stand firm like a wall.
19Ps 78:14 He guided them with the cloud by day and with light from the fire all night.
19Ps 78:15 He split the rocks in the desert and gave them water as abundant as the seas;
19Ps 78:16 he brought streams out of a rocky crag and made water flow down like rivers.
19Ps 78:17 But they continued to sin against him, rebelling in the desert against the Most High.
19Ps 78:18 They willfully put God to the test by demanding the food they craved.
19Ps 78:19 They spoke against God, saying, "Can God spread a table in the desert?
19Ps 78:20 When he struck the rock, water gushed out, and streams flowed abundantly. But can he also give us food? Can he supply meat for his people?"
19Ps 78:21 When the LORD heard them, he was very angry; his fire broke out against Jacob, and his wrath rose against Israel,
19Ps 78:22 for they did not believe in God or trust in his deliverance.
19Ps 78:23 Yet he gave a command to the skies above and opened the doors of the heavens;
19Ps 78:24 he rained down manna for the people to eat, he gave them the grain of heaven.
19Ps 78:25 Men ate the bread of angels; he sent them all the food they could eat.
19Ps 78:26 He let loose the east wind from the heavens and led forth the south wind by his power.
19Ps 78:27 He rained meat down on them like dust, flying birds like sand on the seashore.
19Ps 78:28 He made them come down inside their camp, all around their tents.
19Ps 78:29 They ate till they had more than enough, for he had given them what they craved.
19Ps 78:30 But before they turned from the food they craved, even while it was still in their mouths,
19Ps 78:31 God's anger rose against them; he put to death the sturdiest among them, cutting down the young men of Israel.
19Ps 78:32 In spite of all this, they kept on sinning; in spite of his wonders, they did not believe.
19Ps 78:33 So he ended their days in futility and their years in terror.
19Ps 78:34 Whenever God slew them, they would seek him; they eagerly turned to him again.
19Ps 78:35 They remembered that God was their Rock, that God Most High was their Redeemer.
19Ps 78:36 But then they would flatter him with their mouths, lying to him with their tongues;
19Ps 78:37 their hearts were not loyal to him, they were not faithful to his covenant.
19Ps 78:38 Yet he was merciful; he forgave their iniquities and did not destroy them. Time after time he restrained his anger and did not stir up his full wrath.
19Ps 78:39 He remembered that they were but flesh, a passing breeze that does not return.
19Ps 78:40 How often they rebelled against him in the desert and grieved him in the wasteland!
19Ps 78:41 Again and again they put God to the test; they vexed the Holy One of Israel.
19Ps 78:42 They did not remember his power--the day he redeemed them from the oppressor,
19Ps 78:43 the day he displayed his miraculous signs in Egypt, his wonders in the region of Zoan.
19Ps 78:44 He turned their rivers to blood; they could not drink from their streams.
19Ps 78:45 He sent swarms of flies that devoured them, and frogs that devastated them.
19Ps 78:46 He gave their crops to the grasshopper, their produce to the locust.
19Ps 78:47 He destroyed their vines with hail and their sycamore-figs with sleet.
19Ps 78:48 He gave over their cattle to the hail, their livestock to bolts of lightning.
19Ps 78:49 He unleashed against them his hot anger, his wrath, indignation and hostility--a band of destroying angels.
19Ps 78:50 He prepared a path for his anger; he did not spare them from death but gave them over to the plague.
19Ps 78:51 He struck down all the firstborn of Egypt, the firstfruits of manhood in the tents of Ham.
19Ps 78:52 But he brought his people out like a flock; he led them like sheep through the desert.
19Ps 78:53 He guided them safely, so they were unafraid; but the sea engulfed their enemies.
19Ps 78:54 Thus he brought them to the border of his holy land, to the hill country his right hand had taken.
19Ps 78:55 He drove out nations before them and allotted their lands to them as an inheritance; he settled the tribes of Israel in their homes.
19Ps 78:56 But they put God to the test and rebelled against the Most High; they did not keep his statutes.
