19Ps 95:9 where your fathers tested and tried me, though they had seen what I did.
19Ps 95:10 For forty years I was angry with that generation; I said, "They are a people whose hearts go astray, and they have not known my ways."
19Ps 95:11 So I declared on oath in my anger, "They shall never enter my rest."
19Ps 96:1 Sing to the LORD a new song; sing to the LORD, all the earth.
19Ps 96:2 Sing to the LORD, praise his name; proclaim his salvation day after day.
19Ps 96:3 Declare his glory among the nations, his marvelous deeds among all peoples.
19Ps 96:4 For great is the LORD and most worthy of praise; he is to be feared above all gods.
19Ps 96:5 For all the gods of the nations are idols, but the LORD made the heavens.
19Ps 96:6 Splendor and majesty are before him; strength and glory are in his sanctuary.
19Ps 96:7 Ascribe to the LORD, O families of nations, ascribe to the LORD glory and strength.
19Ps 96:8 Ascribe to the LORD the glory due his name; bring an offering and come into his courts.
19Ps 96:9 Worship the LORD in the splendor of his holiness; tremble before him, all the earth.
19Ps 96:10 Say among the nations, "The LORD reigns." The world is firmly established, it cannot be moved; he will judge the peoples with equity.
19Ps 96:11 Let the heavens rejoice, let the earth be glad; let the sea resound, and all that is in it;
19Ps 96:12 let the fields be jubilant, and everything in them. Then all the trees of the forest will sing for joy;
19Ps 96:13 they will sing before the LORD, for he comes, he comes to judge the earth. He will judge the world in righteousness and the peoples in his truth.
19Ps 97:1 The LORD reigns, let the earth be glad; let the distant shores rejoice.
19Ps 97:2 Clouds and thick darkness surround him; righteousness and justice are the foundation of his throne.
19Ps 97:3 Fire goes before him and consumes his foes on every side.
19Ps 97:4 His lightning lights up the world; the earth sees and trembles.
19Ps 97:5 The mountains melt like wax before the LORD, before the Lord of all the earth.
19Ps 97:6 The heavens proclaim his righteousness, and all the peoples see his glory.
19Ps 97:7 All who worship images are put to shame, those who boast in idols--worship him, all you gods!
19Ps 97:8 Zion hears and rejoices and the villages of Judah are glad because of your judgments, O LORD.
19Ps 97:9 For you, O LORD, are the Most High over all the earth; you are exalted far above all gods.
19Ps 97:10 Let those who love the LORD hate evil, for he guards the lives of his faithful ones and delivers them from the hand of the wicked.
19Ps 97:11 Light is shed upon the righteous and joy on the upright in heart.
19Ps 97:12 Rejoice in the LORD, you who are righteous, and praise his holy name.
19Ps 98:1 A psalm. Sing to the LORD a new song, for he has done marvelous things; his right hand and his holy arm have worked salvation for him.
19Ps 98:2 The LORD has made his salvation known and revealed his righteousness to the nations.
19Ps 98:3 He has remembered his love and his faithfulness to the house of Israel; all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.
19Ps 98:4 Shout for joy to the LORD, all the earth, burst into jubilant song with music;
19Ps 98:5 make music to the LORD with the harp, with the harp and the sound of singing,
19Ps 98:6 with trumpets and the blast of the ram's horn--shout for joy before the LORD, the King.
19Ps 98:7 Let the sea resound, and everything in it, the world, and all who live in it.
19Ps 98:8 Let the rivers clap their hands, let the mountains sing together for joy;
19Ps 98:9 let them sing before the LORD, for he comes to judge the earth. He will judge the world in righteousness and the peoples with equity.
19Ps 99:1 The LORD reigns, let the nations tremble; he sits enthroned between the cherubim, let the earth shake.
19Ps 99:2 Great is the LORD in Zion; he is exalted over all the nations.
19Ps 99:3 Let them praise your great and awesome name--he is holy.
19Ps 99:4 The King is mighty, he loves justice--you have established equity; in Jacob you have done what is just and right.
19Ps 99:5 Exalt the LORD our God and worship at his footstool; he is holy.
19Ps 99:6 Moses and Aaron were among his priests, Samuel was among those who called on his name; they called on the LORD and he answered them.
19Ps 99:7 He spoke to them from the pillar of cloud; they kept his statutes and the decrees he gave them.
19Ps 99:8 O LORD our God, you answered them; you were to Israel a forgiving God, though you punished their misdeeds.
19Ps 99:9 Exalt the LORD our God and worship at his holy mountain, for the LORD our God is holy.
19Ps 100:1 A psalm. For giving thanks. Shout for joy to the LORD, all the earth.
19Ps 100:2 Worship the LORD with gladness; come before him with joyful songs.
19Ps 100:3 Know that the LORD is God. It is he who made us, and we are his; we are his people, the sheep of his pasture.
19Ps 100:4 Enter his gates with thanksgiving and his courts with praise; give thanks to him and praise his name.
19Ps 100:5 For the LORD is good and his love endures forever; his faithfulness continues through all generations.
19Ps 101:1 Of David. A psalm. I will sing of your love and justice; to you, O LORD, I will sing praise.
19Ps 101:2 I will be careful to lead a blameless life--when will you come to me? I will walk in my house with blameless heart.
19Ps 101:3 I will set before my eyes no vile thing. The deeds of faithless men I hate; they will not cling to me.
19Ps 101:4 Men of perverse heart shall be far from me; I will have nothing to do with evil.
19Ps 101:5 Whoever slanders his neighbor in secret, him will I put to silence; whoever has haughty eyes and a proud heart, him will I not endure.
19Ps 101:6 My eyes will be on the faithful in the land, that they may dwell with me; he whose walk is blameless will minister to me.
19Ps 101:7 No one who practices deceit will dwell in my house; no one who speaks falsely will stand in my presence.
19Ps 101:8 Every morning I will put to silence all the wicked in the land; I will cut off every evildoer from the city of the LORD.
19Ps 102:1 A prayer of an afflicted man. When he is faint and pours out his lament before the LORD. Hear my prayer, O LORD; let my cry for help come to you.
19Ps 102:2 Do not hide your face from me when I am in distress. Turn your ear to me; when I call, answer me quickly.
19Ps 102:3 For my days vanish like smoke; my bones burn like glowing embers.
19Ps 102:4 My heart is blighted and withered like grass; I forget to eat my food.
19Ps 102:5 Because of my loud groaning I am reduced to skin and bones.
19Ps 102:6 I am like a desert owl, like an owl among the ruins.
19Ps 102:7 I lie awake; I have become like a bird alone on a roof.
19Ps 102:8 All day long my enemies taunt me; those who rail against me use my name as a curse.
19Ps 102:9 For I eat ashes as my food and mingle my drink with tears
19Ps 102:10 because of your great wrath, for you have taken me up and thrown me aside.
19Ps 102:11 My days are like the evening shadow; I wither away like grass.
19Ps 102:12 But you, O LORD, sit enthroned forever; your renown endures through all generations.
19Ps 102:13 You will arise and have compassion on Zion, for it is time to show favor to her; the appointed time has come.
19Ps 102:14 For her stones are dear to your servants; her very dust moves them to pity.
19Ps 102:15 The nations will fear the name of the LORD, all the kings of the earth will revere your glory.
19Ps 102:16 For the LORD will rebuild Zion and appear in his glory.
19Ps 102:17 He will respond to the prayer of the destitute; he will not despise their plea.
19Ps 102:18 Let this be written for a future generation, that a people not yet created may praise the LORD£º
19Ps 102:19 "The LORD looked down from his sanctuary on high, from heaven he viewed the earth,
19Ps 102:20 to hear the groans of the prisoners and release those condemned to death."
19Ps 102:21 So the name of the LORD will be declared in Zion and his praise in Jerusalem
19Ps 102:22 when the peoples and the kingdoms assemble to worship the LORD.
19Ps 102:23 In the course of my life he broke my strength; he cut short my days.
19Ps 102:24 So I said£º "Do not take me away, O my God, in the midst of my days; your years go on through all generations.
19Ps 102:25 In the beginning you laid the foundations of the earth, and the heavens are the work of your hands.
19Ps 102:26 They will perish, but you remain; they will all wear out like a garment. Like clothing you will change them and they will be discarded.
19Ps 102:27 But you remain the same, and your years will never end.
19Ps 102:28 The children of your servants will live in your presence; their descendants will be established before you."
19Ps 103:1 Of David. Praise the LORD, O my soul; all my inmost being, praise his holy name.
19Ps 103:2 Praise the LORD, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits--
19Ps 103:3 who forgives all your sins and heals all your diseases,
19Ps 103:4 who redeems your life from the pit and crowns you with love and compassion,
19Ps 103:5 who satisfies your desires with good things so that your youth is renewed like the eagle's.
19Ps 103:6 The LORD works righteousness and justice for all the oppressed.
19Ps 103:7 He made known his ways to Moses, his deeds to the people of Israel£º
19Ps 103:8 The LORD is compassionate and gracious, slow to anger, abounding in love.
19Ps 103:9 He will not always accuse, nor will he harbor his anger forever;
19Ps 103:10 he does not treat us as our sins deserve or repay us according to our iniquities.
19Ps 103:11 For as high as the heavens are above the earth, so great is his love for those who fear him;
19Ps 103:12 as far as the east is from the west, so far has he removed our transgressions from us.
19Ps 103:13 As a father has compassion on his children, so the LORD has compassion on those who fear him;
19Ps 103:14 for he knows how we are formed, he remembers that we are dust.
19Ps 103:15 As for man, his days are like grass, he flourishes like a flower of the field;
19Ps 103:16 the wind blows over it and it is gone, and its place remembers it no more.
19Ps 103:17 But from everlasting to everlasting the LORD'S love is with those who fear him, and his righteousness with their children's children--
19Ps 103:18 with those who keep his covenant and remember to obey his precepts.
19Ps 103:19 The LORD has established his throne in heaven, and his kingdom rules over all.
19Ps 103:20 Praise the LORD, you his angels, you mighty ones who do his bidding, who obey his word.
19Ps 103:21 Praise the LORD, all his heavenly hosts, you his servants who do his will.
19Ps 103:22 Praise the LORD, all his works everywhere in his dominion. Praise the LORD, O my soul.
19Ps 104:1 Praise the LORD, O my soul. O LORD my God, you are very great; you are clothed with splendor and majesty.
19Ps 104:2 He wraps himself in light as with a garment; he stretches out the heavens like a tent
19Ps 104:3 and lays the beams of his upper chambers on their waters. He makes the clouds his chariot and rides on the wings of the wind.
19Ps 104:4 He makes winds his messengers, flames of fire his servants.
19Ps 104:5 He set the earth on its foundations; it can never be moved.
19Ps 104:6 You covered it with the deep as with a garment; the waters stood above the mountains.
19Ps 104:7 But at your rebuke the waters fled, at the sound of your thunder they took to flight;
19Ps 104:8 they flowed over the mountains, they went down into the valleys, to the place you assigned for them.
19Ps 104:9 You set a boundary they cannot cross; never again will they cover the earth.
19Ps 104:10 He makes springs pour water into the ravines; it flows between the mountains.
19Ps 104:11 They give water to all the beasts of the field; the wild donkeys quench their thirst.
19Ps 104:12 The birds of the air nest by the waters; they sing among the branches.
19Ps 104:13 He waters the mountains from his upper chambers; the earth is satisfied by the fruit of his work.
19Ps 104:14 He makes grass grow for the cattle, and plants for man to cultivate--bringing forth food from the earth£º
19Ps 104:15 wine that gladdens the heart of man, oil to make his face shine, and bread that sustains his heart.
19Ps 104:16 The trees of the LORD are well watered, the cedars of Lebanon that he planted.
19Ps 104:17 There the birds make their nests; the stork has its home in the pine trees.
19Ps 104:18 The high mountains belong to the wild goats; the crags are a refuge for the coneys.
19Ps 104:19 The moon marks off the seasons, and the sun knows when to go down.
19Ps 104:20 You bring darkness, it becomes night, and all the beasts of the forest prowl.
19Ps 104:21 The lions roar for their prey and seek their food from God.
19Ps 104:22 The sun rises, and they steal away; they return and lie down in their dens.
19Ps 104:23 Then man goes out to his work, to his labor until evening.
19Ps 104:24 How many are your works, O LORD! In wisdom you made them all; the earth is full of your creatures.
19Ps 104:25 There is the sea, vast and spacious, teeming with creatures beyond number--living things both large and small.
19Ps 104:26 There the ships go to and fro, and the leviathan, which you formed to frolic there.
19Ps 104:27 These all look to you to give them their food at the proper time.
19Ps 104:28 When you give it to them, they gather it up; when you open your hand, they are satisfied with good things.
19Ps 104:29 When you hide your face, they are terrified; when you take away their breath, they die and return to the dust.
19Ps 104:30 When you send your Spirit, they are created, and you renew the face of the earth.
19Ps 104:31 May the glory of the LORD endure forever; may the LORD rejoice in his works--
19Ps 104:32 he who looks at the earth, and it trembles, who touches the mountains, and they smoke.
19Ps 104:33 I will sing to the LORD all my life; I will sing praise to my God as long as I live.
19Ps 104:34 May my meditation be pleasing to him, as I rejoice in the LORD.
19Ps 104:35 But may sinners vanish from the earth and the wicked be no more. Praise the LORD, O my soul. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 105:1 Give thanks to the LORD, call on his name; make known among the nations what he has done.
19Ps 105:2 Sing to him, sing praise to him; tell of all his wonderful acts.
19Ps 105:3 Glory in his holy name; let the hearts of those who seek the LORD rejoice.
19Ps 105:4 Look to the LORD and his strength; seek his face always.
19Ps 105:5 Remember the wonders he has done, his miracles, and the judgments he pronounced,
19Ps 105:6 O descendants of Abraham his servant, O sons of Jacob, his chosen ones.
19Ps 105:7 He is the LORD our God; his judgments are in all the earth.
19Ps 105:8 He remembers his covenant forever, the word he commanded, for a thousand generations,
19Ps 105:9 the covenant he made with Abraham, the oath he swore to Isaac.
19Ps 105:10 He confirmed it to Jacob as a decree, to Israel as an everlasting covenant£º
19Ps 105:11 "To you I will give the land of Canaan as the portion you will inherit."
19Ps 105:12 When they were but few in number, few indeed, and strangers in it,
19Ps 105:13 they wandered from nation to nation, from one kingdom to another.
19Ps 105:14 He allowed no one to oppress them; for their sake he rebuked kings£º
19Ps 105:15 "Do not touch my anointed ones; do my prophets no harm."
19Ps 105:16 He called down famine on the land and destroyed all their supplies of food;
19Ps 105:17 and he sent a man before them--Joseph, sold as a slave.
19Ps 105:18 They bruised his feet with shackles, his neck was put in irons,
19Ps 105:19 till what he foretold came to pass, till the word of the LORD proved him true.
19Ps 105:20 The king sent and released him, the ruler of peoples set him free.
19Ps 105:21 He made him master of his household, ruler over all he possessed,
19Ps 105:22 to instruct his princes as he pleased and teach his elders wisdom.
19Ps 105:23 Then Israel entered Egypt; Jacob lived as an alien in the land of Ham.
19Ps 105:24 The LORD made his people very fruitful; he made them too numerous for their foes,
19Ps 105:25 whose hearts he turned to hate his people, to conspire against his servants.
19Ps 105:26 He sent Moses his servant, and Aaron, whom he had chosen.
19Ps 105:27 They performed his miraculous signs among them, his wonders in the land of Ham.
19Ps 105:28 He sent darkness and made the land dark--for had they not rebelled against his words?
19Ps 105:29 He turned their waters into blood, causing their fish to die.
19Ps 105:30 Their land teemed with frogs, which went up into the bedrooms of their rulers.
19Ps 105:31 He spoke, and there came swarms of flies, and gnats throughout their country.
19Ps 105:32 He turned their rain into hail, with lightning throughout their land;
19Ps 105:33 he struck down their vines and fig trees and shattered the trees of their country.
19Ps 105:34 He spoke, and the locusts came, grasshoppers without number;
19Ps 105:35 they ate up every green thing in their land, ate up the produce of their soil.
19Ps 105:36 Then he struck down all the firstborn in their land, the firstfruits of all their manhood.
19Ps 105:37 He brought out Israel, laden with silver and gold, and from among their tribes no one faltered.
19Ps 105:38 Egypt was glad when they left, because dread of Israel had fallen on them.
19Ps 105:39 He spread out a cloud as a covering, and a fire to give light at night.
19Ps 105:40 They asked, and he brought them quail and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.
19Ps 105:41 He opened the rock, and water gushed out; like a river it flowed in the desert.
19Ps 105:42 For he remembered his holy promise given to his servant Abraham.
19Ps 105:43 He brought out his people with rejoicing, his chosen ones with shouts of joy;
19Ps 105:44 he gave them the lands of the nations, and they fell heir to what others had toiled for--
19Ps 105:45 that they might keep his precepts and observe his laws. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 106:1 Praise the LORD. Give thanks to the LORD, for he is good; his love endures forever.
19Ps 106:2 Who can proclaim the mighty acts of the LORD or fully declare his praise?
19Ps 106:3 Blessed are they who maintain justice, who constantly do what is right.
19Ps 106:4 Remember me, O LORD, when you show favor to your people, come to my aid when you save them,
19Ps 106:5 that I may enjoy the prosperity of your chosen ones, that I may share in the joy of your nation and join your inheritance in giving praise.
19Ps 106:6 We have sinned, even as our fathers did; we have done wrong and acted wickedly.
19Ps 106:7 When our fathers were in Egypt, they gave no thought to your miracles; they did not remember your many kindnesses, and they rebelled by the sea, the Red Sea.
19Ps 106:8 Yet he saved them for his name's sake, to make his mighty power known.
19Ps 106:9 He rebuked the Red Sea, and it dried up; he led them through the depths as through a desert.
19Ps 106:10 He saved them from the hand of the foe; from the hand of the enemy he redeemed them.
19Ps 106:11 The waters covered their adversaries; not one of them survived.
19Ps 106:12 Then they believed his promises and sang his praise.
19Ps 106:13 But they soon forgot what he had done and did not wait for his counsel.
19Ps 106:14 In the desert they gave in to their craving; in the wasteland they put God to the test.
19Ps 106:15 So he gave them what they asked for, but sent a wasting disease upon them.
19Ps 106:16 In the camp they grew envious of Moses and of Aaron, who was consecrated to the LORD.
19Ps 106:17 The earth opened up and swallowed Dathan; it buried the company of Abiram.
19Ps 106:18 Fire blazed among their followers; a flame consumed the wicked.
19Ps 106:19 At Horeb they made a calf and worshiped an idol cast from metal.
19Ps 106:20 They exchanged their Glory for an image of a bull, which eats grass.
19Ps 106:21 They forgot the God who saved them, who had done great things in Egypt,
19Ps 106:22 miracles in the land of Ham and awesome deeds by the Red Sea.
19Ps 106:23 So he said he would destroy them--had not Moses, his chosen one, stood in the breach before him to keep his wrath from destroying them.
19Ps 106:24 Then they despised the pleasant land; they did not believe his promise.
19Ps 106:25 They grumbled in their tents and did not obey the LORD.
19Ps 106:26 So he swore to them with uplifted hand that he would make them fall in the desert,
19Ps 106:27 make their descendants fall among the nations and scatter them throughout the lands.
19Ps 106:28 They yoked themselves to the Baal of Peor and ate sacrifices offered to lifeless gods;
19Ps 106:29 they provoked the LORD to anger by their wicked deeds, and a plague broke out among them.
19Ps 106:30 But Phinehas stood up and intervened, and the plague was checked.
19Ps 106:31 This was credited to him as righteousness for endless generations to come.
19Ps 106:32 By the waters of Meribah they angered the LORD, and trouble came to Moses because of them;
19Ps 106:33 for they rebelled against the Spirit of God, and rash words came from Moses' lips.
19Ps 106:34 They did not destroy the peoples as the LORD had commanded them,
19Ps 106:35 but they mingled with the nations and adopted their customs.
19Ps 106:36 They worshiped their idols, which became a snare to them.
19Ps 106:37 They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to demons.
19Ps 106:38 They shed innocent blood, the blood of their sons and daughters, whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan, and the land was desecrated by their blood.
19Ps 106:39 They defiled themselves by what they did; by their deeds they prostituted themselves.
19Ps 106:40 Therefore the LORD was angry with his people and abhorred his inheritance.
19Ps 106:41 He handed them over to the nations, and their foes ruled over them.
19Ps 106:42 Their enemies oppressed them and subjected them to their power.
19Ps 106:43 Many times he delivered them, but they were bent on rebellion and they wasted away in their sin.
19Ps 106:44 But he took note of their distress when he heard their cry;
19Ps 106:45 for their sake he remembered his covenant and out of his great love he relented.
19Ps 106:46 He caused them to be pitied by all who held them captive.
19Ps 106:47 Save us, O LORD our God, and gather us from the nations, that we may give thanks to your holy name and glory in your praise.
19Ps 106:48 Praise be to the LORD, the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting. Let all the people say, "Amen!" Praise the LORD.
19Ps 107:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for he is good; his love endures forever.
19Ps 107:2 Let the redeemed of the LORD say this--those he redeemed from the hand of the foe,
19Ps 107:3 those he gathered from the lands, from east and west, from north and south.
19Ps 107:4 Some wandered in desert wastelands, finding no way to a city where they could settle.
19Ps 107:5 They were hungry and thirsty, and their lives ebbed away.
19Ps 107:6 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress.
19Ps 107:7 He led them by a straight way to a city where they could settle.
19Ps 107:8 Let them give thanks to the LORD for his unfailing love and his wonderful deeds for men,
19Ps 107:9 for he satisfies the thirsty and fills the hungry with good things.
19Ps 107:10 Some sat in darkness and the deepest gloom, prisoners suffering in iron chains,
19Ps 107:11 for they had rebelled against the words of God and despised the counsel of the Most High.
19Ps 107:12 So he subjected them to bitter labor; they stumbled, and there was no one to help.
19Ps 107:13 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, and he saved them from their distress.
19Ps 107:14 He brought them out of darkness and the deepest gloom and broke away their chains.
19Ps 107:15 Let them give thanks to the LORD for his unfailing love and his wonderful deeds for men,
19Ps 107:16 for he breaks down gates of bronze and cuts through bars of iron.
19Ps 107:17 Some became fools through their rebellious ways and suffered affliction because of their iniquities.
19Ps 107:18 They loathed all food and drew near the gates of death.
19Ps 107:19 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, and he saved them from their distress.
19Ps 107:20 He sent forth his word and healed them; he rescued them from the grave.
19Ps 107:21 Let them give thanks to the LORD for his unfailing love and his wonderful deeds for men.
19Ps 107:22 Let them sacrifice thank offerings and tell of his works with songs of joy.
19Ps 107:23 Others went out on the sea in ships; they were merchants on the mighty waters.
19Ps 107:24 They saw the works of the LORD, his wonderful deeds in the deep.
19Ps 107:25 For he spoke and stirred up a tempest that lifted high the waves.
19Ps 107:26 They mounted up to the heavens and went down to the depths; in their peril their courage melted away.
19Ps 107:27 They reeled and staggered like drunken men; they were at their wits' end.
19Ps 107:28 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and he brought them out of their distress.
19Ps 107:29 He stilled the storm to a whisper; the waves of the sea were hushed.
19Ps 107:30 They were glad when it grew calm, and he guided them to their desired haven.
19Ps 107:31 Let them give thanks to the LORD for his unfailing love and his wonderful deeds for men.
19Ps 107:32 Let them exalt him in the assembly of the people and praise him in the council of the elders.
19Ps 107:33 He turned rivers into a desert, flowing springs into thirsty ground,
19Ps 107:34 and fruitful land into a salt waste, because of the wickedness of those who lived there.
19Ps 107:35 He turned the desert into pools of water and the parched ground into flowing springs;
19Ps 107:36 there he brought the hungry to live, and they founded a city where they could settle.
19Ps 107:37 They sowed fields and planted vineyards that yielded a fruitful harvest;
19Ps 107:38 he blessed them, and their numbers greatly increased, and he did not let their herds diminish.
19Ps 107:39 Then their numbers decreased, and they were humbled by oppression, calamity and sorrow;
19Ps 107:40 he who pours contempt on nobles made them wander in a trackless waste.
19Ps 107:41 But he lifted the needy out of their affliction and increased their families like flocks.
19Ps 107:42 The upright see and rejoice, but all the wicked shut their mouths.
19Ps 107:43 Whoever is wise, let him heed these things and consider the great love of the LORD.
19Ps 108:1 A song. A psalm of David. My heart is steadfast, O God; I will sing and make music with all my soul.
19Ps 108:2 Awake, harp and lyre! I will awaken the dawn.
19Ps 108:3 I will praise you, O LORD, among the nations; I will sing of you among the peoples.
19Ps 108:4 For great is your love, higher than the heavens; your faithfulness reaches to the skies.
19Ps 108:5 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens, and let your glory be over all the earth.
19Ps 108:6 Save us and help us with your right hand, that those you love may be delivered.
19Ps 108:7 God has spoken from his sanctuary£º "In triumph I will parcel out Shechem and measure off the Valley of Succoth.
19Ps 108:8 Gilead is mine, Manasseh is mine; Ephraim is my helmet, Judah my scepter.
19Ps 108:9 Moab is my washbasin, upon Edom I toss my sandal; over Philistia I shout in triumph."
19Ps 108:10 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?
19Ps 108:11 Is it not you, O God, you who have rejected us and no longer go out with our armies?
19Ps 108:12 Give us aid against the enemy, for the help of man is worthless.
19Ps 108:13 With God we will gain the victory, and he will trample down our enemies.
19Ps 109:1 For the director of music. Of David. A psalm. O God, whom I praise, do not remain silent,
19Ps 109:2 for wicked and deceitful men have opened their mouths against me; they have spoken against me with lying tongues.
19Ps 109:3 With words of hatred they surround me; they attack me without cause.
19Ps 109:4 In return for my friendship they accuse me, but I am a man of prayer.
19Ps 109:5 They repay me evil for good, and hatred for my friendship.
19Ps 109:6 Appoint an evil man to oppose him; let an accuser stand at his right hand.
19Ps 109:7 When he is tried, let him be found guilty, and may his prayers condemn him.
19Ps 109:8 May his days be few; may another take his place of leadership.
19Ps 109:9 May his children be fatherless and his wife a widow.
19Ps 109:10 May his children be wandering beggars; may they be driven from their ruined homes.
19Ps 109:11 May a creditor seize all he has; may strangers plunder the fruits of his labor.
19Ps 109:12 May no one extend kindness to him or take pity on his fatherless children.
19Ps 109:13 May his descendants be cut off, their names blotted out from the next generation.
19Ps 109:14 May the iniquity of his fathers be remembered before the LORD; may the sin of his mother never be blotted out.
19Ps 109:15 May their sins always remain before the LORD, that he may cut off the memory of them from the earth.
19Ps 109:16 For he never thought of doing a kindness, but hounded to death the poor and the needy and the brokenhearted.
19Ps 109:17 He loved to pronounce a curse--may it come on him; he found no pleasure in blessing--may it be far from him.
19Ps 109:18 He wore cursing as his garment; it entered into his body like water, into his bones like oil.
