19Ps 119:1 Blessed are they whose ways are blameless, who walk according to the law of the LORD.
19Ps 119:2 Blessed are they who keep his statutes and seek him with all their heart.
19Ps 119:3 They do nothing wrong; they walk in his ways.
19Ps 119:4 You have laid down precepts that are to be fully obeyed.
19Ps 119:5 Oh, that my ways were steadfast in obeying your decrees!
19Ps 119:6 Then I would not be put to shame when I consider all your commands.
19Ps 119:7 I will praise you with an upright heart as I learn your righteous laws.
19Ps 119:8 I will obey your decrees; do not utterly forsake me.
19Ps 119:9 How can a young man keep his way pure? By living according to your word.
19Ps 119:10 I seek you with all my heart; do not let me stray from your commands.
19Ps 119:11 I have hidden your word in my heart that I might not sin against you.
19Ps 119:12 Praise be to you, O LORD; teach me your decrees.
19Ps 119:13 With my lips I recount all the laws that come from your mouth.
19Ps 119:14 I rejoice in following your statutes as one rejoices in great riches.
19Ps 119:15 I meditate on your precepts and consider your ways.
19Ps 119:16 I delight in your decrees; I will not neglect your word.
19Ps 119:17 Do good to your servant, and I will live; I will obey your word.
19Ps 119:18 Open my eyes that I may see wonderful things in your law.
19Ps 119:19 I am a stranger on earth; do not hide your commands from me.
19Ps 119:20 My soul is consumed with longing for your laws at all times.
19Ps 119:21 You rebuke the arrogant, who are cursed and who stray from your commands.
19Ps 119:22 Remove from me scorn and contempt, for I keep your statutes.
19Ps 119:23 Though rulers sit together and slander me, your servant will meditate on your decrees.
19Ps 119:24 Your statutes are my delight; they are my counselors.
19Ps 119:25 I am laid low in the dust; preserve my life according to your word.
19Ps 119:26 I recounted my ways and you answered me; teach me your decrees.
19Ps 119:27 Let me understand the teaching of your precepts; then I will meditate on your wonders.
19Ps 119:28 My soul is weary with sorrow; strengthen me according to your word.
19Ps 119:29 Keep me from deceitful ways; be gracious to me through your law.
19Ps 119:30 I have chosen the way of truth; I have set my heart on your laws.
19Ps 119:31 I hold fast to your statutes, O LORD; do not let me be put to shame.
19Ps 119:32 I run in the path of your commands, for you have set my heart free.
19Ps 119:33 Teach me, O LORD, to follow your decrees; then I will keep them to the end.
19Ps 119:34 Give me understanding, and I will keep your law and obey it with all my heart.
19Ps 119:35 Direct me in the path of your commands, for there I find delight.
19Ps 119:36 Turn my heart toward your statutes and not toward selfish gain.
19Ps 119:37 Turn my eyes away from worthless things; preserve my life according to your word.
19Ps 119:38 Fulfill your promise to your servant, so that you may be feared.
19Ps 119:39 Take away the disgrace I dread, for your laws are good.
19Ps 119:40 How I long for your precepts! Preserve my life in your righteousness.
19Ps 119:41 May your unfailing love come to me, O LORD, your salvation according to your promise;
19Ps 119:42 then I will answer the one who taunts me, for I trust in your word.
19Ps 119:43 Do not snatch the word of truth from my mouth, for I have put my hope in your laws.
19Ps 119:44 I will always obey your law, for ever and ever.
19Ps 119:45 I will walk about in freedom, for I have sought out your precepts.
19Ps 119:46 I will speak of your statutes before kings and will not be put to shame,
19Ps 119:47 for I delight in your commands because I love them.
19Ps 119:48 I lift up my hands to your commands, which I love, and I meditate on your decrees.
19Ps 119:49 Remember your word to your servant, for you have given me hope.
19Ps 119:50 My comfort in my suffering is this£º Your promise preserves my life.
19Ps 119:51 The arrogant mock me without restraint, but I do not turn from your law.
19Ps 119:52 I remember your ancient laws, O LORD, and I find comfort in them.
19Ps 119:53 Indignation grips me because of the wicked, who have forsaken your law.
19Ps 119:54 Your decrees are the theme of my song wherever I lodge.
19Ps 119:55 In the night I remember your name, O LORD, and I will keep your law.
19Ps 119:56 This has been my practice£º I obey your precepts.
19Ps 119:57 You are my portion, O LORD; I have promised to obey your words.
19Ps 119:58 I have sought your face with all my heart; be gracious to me according to your promise.
19Ps 119:59 I have considered my ways and have turned my steps to your statutes.
19Ps 119:60 I will hasten and not delay to obey your commands.
19Ps 119:61 Though the wicked bind me with ropes, I will not forget your law.
19Ps 119:62 At midnight I rise to give you thanks for your righteous laws.
19Ps 119:63 I am a friend to all who fear you, to all who follow your precepts.
19Ps 119:64 The earth is filled with your love, O LORD; teach me your decrees.
19Ps 119:65 Do good to your servant according to your word, O LORD.
19Ps 119:66 Teach me knowledge and good judgment, for I believe in your commands.
19Ps 119:67 Before I was afflicted I went astray, but now I obey your word.
19Ps 119:68 You are good, and what you do is good; teach me your decrees.
19Ps 119:69 Though the arrogant have smeared me with lies, I keep your precepts with all my heart.
19Ps 119:70 Their hearts are callous and unfeeling, but I delight in your law.
19Ps 119:71 It was good for me to be afflicted so that I might learn your decrees.
19Ps 119:72 The law from your mouth is more precious to me than thousands of pieces of silver and gold.
19Ps 119:73 Your hands made me and formed me; give me understanding to learn your commands.
19Ps 119:74 May those who fear you rejoice when they see me, for I have put my hope in your word.
19Ps 119:75 I know, O LORD, that your laws are righteous, and in faithfulness you have afflicted me.
19Ps 119:76 May your unfailing love be my comfort, according to your promise to your servant.
19Ps 119:77 Let your compassion come to me that I may live, for your law is my delight.
19Ps 119:78 May the arrogant be put to shame for wronging me without cause; but I will meditate on your precepts.
19Ps 119:79 May those who fear you turn to me, those who understand your statutes.
19Ps 119:80 May my heart be blameless toward your decrees, that I may not be put to shame.
19Ps 119:81 My soul faints with longing for your salvation, but I have put my hope in your word.
19Ps 119:82 My eyes fail, looking for your promise; I say, "When will you comfort me?"
19Ps 119:83 Though I am like a wineskin in the smoke, I do not forget your decrees.
19Ps 119:84 How long must your servant wait? When will you punish my persecutors?
19Ps 119:85 The arrogant dig pitfalls for me, contrary to your law.
19Ps 119:86 All your commands are trustworthy; help me, for men persecute me without cause.
19Ps 119:87 They almost wiped me from the earth, but I have not forsaken your precepts.
19Ps 119:88 Preserve my life according to your love, and I will obey the statutes of your mouth.
19Ps 119:89 Your word, O LORD, is eternal; it stands firm in the heavens.
19Ps 119:90 Your faithfulness continues through all generations; you established the earth, and it endures.
19Ps 119:91 Your laws endure to this day, for all things serve you.
19Ps 119:92 If your law had not been my delight, I would have perished in my affliction.
19Ps 119:93 I will never forget your precepts, for by them you have preserved my life.
19Ps 119:94 Save me, for I am yours; I have sought out your precepts.
19Ps 119:95 The wicked are waiting to destroy me, but I will ponder your statutes.
19Ps 119:96 To all perfection I see a limit; but your commands are boundless.
19Ps 119:97 Oh, how I love your law! I meditate on it all day long.
19Ps 119:98 Your commands make me wiser than my enemies, for they are ever with me.
19Ps 119:99 I have more insight than all my teachers, for I meditate on your statutes.
19Ps 119:100 I have more understanding than the elders, for I obey your precepts.
19Ps 119:101 I have kept my feet from every evil path so that I might obey your word.
19Ps 119:102 I have not departed from your laws, for you yourself have taught me.
19Ps 119:103 How sweet are your words to my taste, sweeter than honey to my mouth!
19Ps 119:104 I gain understanding from your precepts; therefore I hate every wrong path.
19Ps 119:105 Your word is a lamp to my feet and a light for my path.
19Ps 119:106 I have taken an oath and confirmed it, that I will follow your righteous laws.
19Ps 119:107 I have suffered much; preserve my life, O LORD, according to your word.
19Ps 119:108 Accept, O LORD, the willing praise of my mouth, and teach me your laws.
19Ps 119:109 Though I constantly take my life in my hands, I will not forget your law.
19Ps 119:110 The wicked have set a snare for me, but I have not strayed from your precepts.
19Ps 119:111 Your statutes are my heritage forever; they are the joy of my heart.
19Ps 119:112 My heart is set on keeping your decrees to the very end.
19Ps 119:113 I hate double-minded men, but I love your law.
19Ps 119:114 You are my refuge and my shield; I have put my hope in your word.
19Ps 119:115 Away from me, you evildoers, that I may keep the commands of my God!
19Ps 119:116 Sustain me according to your promise, and I will live; do not let my hopes be dashed.
19Ps 119:117 Uphold me, and I will be delivered; I will always have regard for your decrees.
19Ps 119:118 You reject all who stray from your decrees, for their deceitfulness is in vain.
19Ps 119:119 All the wicked of the earth you discard like dross; therefore I love your statutes.
19Ps 119:120 My flesh trembles in fear of you; I stand in awe of your laws.
19Ps 119:121 I have done what is righteous and just; do not leave me to my oppressors.
