19Ps 119:138 The statutes you have laid down are righteous; they are fully trustworthy.
19Ps 119:139 My zeal wears me out, for my enemies ignore your words.
19Ps 119:140 Your promises have been thoroughly tested, and your servant loves them.
19Ps 119:141 Though I am lowly and despised, I do not forget your precepts.
19Ps 119:142 Your righteousness is everlasting and your law is true.
19Ps 119:143 Trouble and distress have come upon me, but your commands are my delight.
19Ps 119:144 Your statutes are forever right; give me understanding that I may live.
19Ps 119:145 I call with all my heart; answer me, O LORD, and I will obey your decrees.
19Ps 119:146 I call out to you; save me and I will keep your statutes.
19Ps 119:147 I rise before dawn and cry for help; I have put my hope in your word.
19Ps 119:148 My eyes stay open through the watches of the night, that I may meditate on your promises.
