19Ps 123:4 We have endured much ridicule from the proud, much contempt from the arrogant.
19Ps 124:1 A song of ascents. Of David. If the LORD had not been on our side--let Israel say--
19Ps 124:2 if the LORD had not been on our side when men attacked us,
19Ps 124:3 when their anger flared against us, they would have swallowed us alive;
19Ps 124:4 the flood would have engulfed us, the torrent would have swept over us,
19Ps 124:5 the raging waters would have swept us away.
19Ps 124:6 Praise be to the LORD, who has not let us be torn by their teeth.
19Ps 124:7 We have escaped like a bird out of the fowler's snare; the snare has been broken, and we have escaped.
19Ps 124:8 Our help is in the name of the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.
19Ps 125:1 A song of ascents. Those who trust in the LORD are like Mount Zion, which cannot be shaken but endures forever.
19Ps 125:2 As the mountains surround Jerusalem, so the LORD surrounds his people both now and forevermore.
19Ps 125:3 The scepter of the wicked will not remain over the land allotted to the righteous, for then the righteous might use their hands to do evil.
19Ps 125:4 Do good, O LORD, to those who are good, to those who are upright in heart.
19Ps 125:5 But those who turn to crooked ways the LORD will banish with the evildoers. Peace be upon Israel.
19Ps 126:1 A song of ascents. When the LORD brought back the captives to Zion, we were like men who dreamed.
19Ps 126:2 Our mouths were filled with laughter, our tongues with songs of joy. Then it was said among the nations, "The LORD has done great things for them."
19Ps 126:3 The LORD has done great things for us, and we are filled with joy.
19Ps 126:4 Restore our fortunes, O LORD, like streams in the Negev.
19Ps 126:5 Those who sow in tears will reap with songs of joy.
19Ps 126:6 He who goes out weeping, carrying seed to sow, will return with songs of joy, carrying sheaves with him.
19Ps 127:1 A song of ascents. Of Solomon. Unless the LORD builds the house, its builders labor in vain. Unless the LORD watches over the city, the watchmen stand guard in vain.
19Ps 127:2 In vain you rise early and stay up late, toiling for food to eat--for he grants sleep to those he loves.
19Ps 127:3 Sons are a heritage from the LORD, children a reward from him.
19Ps 127:4 Like arrows in the hands of a warrior are sons born in one's youth.
19Ps 127:5 Blessed is the man whose quiver is full of them. They will not be put to shame when they contend with their enemies in the gate.
19Ps 128:1 A song of ascents. Blessed are all who fear the LORD, who walk in his ways.
19Ps 128:2 You will eat the fruit of your labor; blessings and prosperity will be yours.
19Ps 128:3 Your wife will be like a fruitful vine within your house; your sons will be like olive shoots around your table.
19Ps 128:4 Thus is the man blessed who fears the LORD.
19Ps 128:5 May the LORD bless you from Zion all the days of your life; may you see the prosperity of Jerusalem,
19Ps 128:6 and may you live to see your children's children. Peace be upon Israel.
19Ps 129:1 A song of ascents. They have greatly oppressed me from my youth--let Israel say--
19Ps 129:2 they have greatly oppressed me from my youth, but they have not gained the victory over me.
19Ps 129:3 Plowmen have plowed my back and made their furrows long.
19Ps 129:4 But the LORD is righteous; he has cut me free from the cords of the wicked.
19Ps 129:5 May all who hate Zion be turned back in shame.
19Ps 129:6 May they be like grass on the roof, which withers before it can grow;
19Ps 129:7 with it the reaper cannot fill his hands, nor the one who gathers fill his arms.
19Ps 129:8 May those who pass by not say, "The blessing of the LORD be upon you; we bless you in the name of the LORD."
19Ps 130:1 A song of ascents. Out of the depths I cry to you, O LORD;
19Ps 130:2 O Lord, hear my voice. Let your ears be attentive to my cry for mercy.
19Ps 130:3 If you, O LORD, kept a record of sins, O Lord, who could stand?
19Ps 130:4 But with you there is forgiveness; therefore you are feared.
19Ps 130:5 I wait for the LORD, my soul waits, and in his word I put my hope.
19Ps 130:6 My soul waits for the Lord more than watchmen wait for the morning, more than watchmen wait for the morning.
19Ps 130:7 O Israel, put your hope in the LORD, for with the LORD is unfailing love and with him is full redemption.
19Ps 130:8 He himself will redeem Israel from all their sins.
19Ps 131:1 A song of ascents. Of David. My heart is not proud, O LORD, my eyes are not haughty; I do not concern myself with great matters or things too wonderful for me.
19Ps 131:2 But I have stilled and quieted my soul; like a weaned child with its mother, like a weaned child is my soul within me.
19Ps 131:3 O Israel, put your hope in the LORD both now and forevermore.
19Ps 132:1 A song of ascents. O LORD, remember David and all the hardships he endured.
19Ps 132:2 He swore an oath to the LORD and made a vow to the Mighty One of Jacob£º
19Ps 132:3 "I will not enter my house or go to my bed--
19Ps 132:4 I will allow no sleep to my eyes, no slumber to my eyelids,
19Ps 132:5 till I find a place for the LORD, a dwelling for the Mighty One of Jacob."
19Ps 132:6 We heard it in Ephrathah, we came upon it in the fields of Jaar£º
19Ps 132:7 "Let us go to his dwelling place; let us worship at his footstool--
19Ps 132:8 arise, O LORD, and come to your resting place, you and the ark of your might.
19Ps 132:9 May your priests be clothed with righteousness; may your saints sing for joy."
19Ps 132:10 For the sake of David your servant, do not reject your anointed one.
19Ps 132:11 The LORD swore an oath to David, a sure oath that he will not revoke£º "One of your own descendants I will place on your throne--
19Ps 132:12 if your sons keep my covenant and the statutes I teach them, then their sons will sit on your throne for ever and ever."
19Ps 132:13 For the LORD has chosen Zion, he has desired it for his dwelling£º
19Ps 132:14 "This is my resting place for ever and ever; here I will sit enthroned, for I have desired it--
19Ps 132:15 I will bless her with abundant provisions; her poor will I satisfy with food.
19Ps 132:16 I will clothe her priests with salvation, and her saints will ever sing for joy.
19Ps 132:17 "Here I will make a horn grow for David and set up a lamp for my anointed one.
19Ps 132:18 I will clothe his enemies with shame, but the crown on his head will be resplendent."
19Ps 133:1 A song of ascents. Of David. How good and pleasant it is when brothers live together in unity!
19Ps 133:2 It is like precious oil poured on the head, running down on the beard, running down on Aaron's beard, down upon the collar of his robes.
19Ps 133:3 It is as if the dew of Hermon were falling on Mount Zion. For there the LORD bestows his blessing, even life forevermore.
19Ps 134:1 A song of ascents. Praise the LORD, all you servants of the LORD who minister by night in the house of the LORD.
19Ps 134:2 Lift up your hands in the sanctuary and praise the LORD.
19Ps 134:3 May the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth, bless you from Zion.
19Ps 135:1 Praise the LORD. Praise the name of the LORD; praise him, you servants of the LORD,
19Ps 135:2 you who minister in the house of the LORD, in the courts of the house of our God.
19Ps 135:3 Praise the LORD, for the LORD is good; sing praise to his name, for that is pleasant.
19Ps 135:4 For the LORD has chosen Jacob to be his own, Israel to be his treasured possession.
19Ps 135:5 I know that the LORD is great, that our Lord is greater than all gods.
19Ps 135:6 The LORD does whatever pleases him, in the heavens and on the earth, in the seas and all their depths.
19Ps 135:7 He makes clouds rise from the ends of the earth; he sends lightning with the rain and brings out the wind from his storehouses.
19Ps 135:8 He struck down the firstborn of Egypt, the firstborn of men and animals.
19Ps 135:9 He sent his signs and wonders into your midst, O Egypt, against Pharaoh and all his servants.
19Ps 135:10 He struck down many nations and killed mighty kings--
19Ps 135:11 Sihon king of the Amorites, Og king of Bashan and all the kings of Canaan--
19Ps 135:12 and he gave their land as an inheritance, an inheritance to his people Israel.
19Ps 135:13 Your name, O LORD, endures forever, your renown, O LORD, through all generations.
19Ps 135:14 For the LORD will vindicate his people and have compassion on his servants.
19Ps 135:15 The idols of the nations are silver and gold, made by the hands of men.
19Ps 135:16 They have mouths, but cannot speak, eyes, but they cannot see;
19Ps 135:17 they have ears, but cannot hear, nor is there breath in their mouths.
19Ps 135:18 Those who make them will be like them, and so will all who trust in them.
19Ps 135:19 O house of Israel, praise the LORD; O house of Aaron, praise the LORD;
19Ps 135:20 O house of Levi, praise the LORD; you who fear him, praise the LORD.
19Ps 135:21 Praise be to the LORD from Zion, to him who dwells in Jerusalem. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 136:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for he is good. His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:2 Give thanks to the God of gods. His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:3 Give thanks to the Lord of lords£º His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:4 to him who alone does great wonders, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:5 who by his understanding made the heavens, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:6 who spread out the earth upon the waters, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:7 who made the great lights--His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:8 the sun to govern the day, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:9 the moon and stars to govern the night; His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:10 to him who struck down the firstborn of Egypt His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:11 and brought Israel out from among them His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:12 with a mighty hand and outstretched arm; His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:13 to him who divided the Red Sea asunder His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:14 and brought Israel through the midst of it, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:15 but swept Pharaoh and his army into the Red Sea; His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:16 to him who led his people through the desert, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:17 who struck down great kings, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:18 and killed mighty kings--His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:19 Sihon king of the Amorites His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:20 and Og king of Bashan--His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:21 and gave their land as an inheritance, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:22 an inheritance to his servant Israel; His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:23 to the One who remembered us in our low estate His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:24 and freed us from our enemies, His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:25 and who gives food to every creature. His love endures forever.
19Ps 136:26 Give thanks to the God of heaven. His love endures forever.
19Ps 137:1 By the rivers of Babylon we sat and wept when we remembered Zion.
19Ps 137:2 There on the poplars we hung our harps,
19Ps 137:3 for there our captors asked us for songs, our tormentors demanded songs of joy; they said, "Sing us one of the songs of Zion!"
19Ps 137:4 How can we sing the songs of the LORD while in a foreign land?
19Ps 137:5 If I forget you, O Jerusalem, may my right hand forget its skill.
19Ps 137:6 May my tongue cling to the roof of my mouth if I do not remember you, if I do not consider Jerusalem my highest joy.
19Ps 137:7 Remember, O LORD, what the Edomites did on the day Jerusalem fell. "Tear it down," they cried, "tear it down to its foundations!"
19Ps 137:8 O Daughter of Babylon, doomed to destruction, happy is he who repays you for what you have done to us--
19Ps 137:9 he who seizes your infants and dashes them against the rocks.
19Ps 138:1 Of David. I will praise you, O LORD, with all my heart; before the "gods" I will sing your praise.
19Ps 138:2 I will bow down toward your holy temple and will praise your name for your love and your faithfulness, for you have exalted above all things your name and your word.
19Ps 138:3 When I called, you answered me; you made me bold and stouthearted.
19Ps 138:4 May all the kings of the earth praise you, O LORD, when they hear the words of your mouth.
19Ps 138:5 May they sing of the ways of the LORD, for the glory of the LORD is great.
19Ps 138:6 Though the LORD is on high, he looks upon the lowly, but the proud he knows from afar.
19Ps 138:7 Though I walk in the midst of trouble, you preserve my life; you stretch out your hand against the anger of my foes, with your right hand you save me.
19Ps 138:8 The LORD will fulfill his purpose for me; your love, O LORD, endures forever--do not abandon the works of your hands.
19Ps 139:1 For the director of music. Of David. A psalm. O LORD, you have searched me and you know me.
19Ps 139:2 You know when I sit and when I rise; you perceive my thoughts from afar.
19Ps 139:3 You discern my going out and my lying down; you are familiar with all my ways.
19Ps 139:4 Before a word is on my tongue you know it completely, O LORD.
19Ps 139:5 You hem me in--behind and before; you have laid your hand upon me.
19Ps 139:6 Such knowledge is too wonderful for me, too lofty for me to attain.
19Ps 139:7 Where can I go from your Spirit? Where can I flee from your presence?
19Ps 139:8 If I go up to the heavens, you are there; if I make my bed in the depths, you are there.
19Ps 139:9 If I rise on the wings of the dawn, if I settle on the far side of the sea,
19Ps 139:10 even there your hand will guide me, your right hand will hold me fast.
19Ps 139:11 If I say, "Surely the darkness will hide me and the light become night around me,"
19Ps 139:12 even the darkness will not be dark to you; the night will shine like the day, for darkness is as light to you.
19Ps 139:13 For you created my inmost being; you knit me together in my mother's womb.
19Ps 139:14 I praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made; your works are wonderful, I know that full well.
19Ps 139:15 My frame was not hidden from you when I was made in the secret place. When I was woven together in the depths of the earth,
19Ps 139:16 your eyes saw my unformed body. All the days ordained for me were written in your book before one of them came to be.
19Ps 139:17 How precious to me are your thoughts, O God! How vast is the sum of them!
19Ps 139:18 Were I to count them, they would outnumber the grains of sand. When I awake, I am still with you.
19Ps 139:19 If only you would slay the wicked, O God! Away from me, you bloodthirsty men!
19Ps 139:20 They speak of you with evil intent; your adversaries misuse your name.
19Ps 139:21 Do I not hate those who hate you, O LORD, and abhor those who rise up against you?
19Ps 139:22 I have nothing but hatred for them; I count them my enemies.
19Ps 139:23 Search me, O God, and know my heart; test me and know my anxious thoughts.
19Ps 139:24 See if there is any offensive way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.
19Ps 140:1 For the director of music. A psalm of David. Rescue me, O LORD, from evil men; protect me from men of violence,
19Ps 140:2 who devise evil plans in their hearts and stir up war every day.
19Ps 140:3 They make their tongues as sharp as a serpent's; the poison of vipers is on their lips. Selah
19Ps 140:4 Keep me, O LORD, from the hands of the wicked; protect me from men of violence who plan to trip my feet.
19Ps 140:5 Proud men have hidden a snare for me; they have spread out the cords of their net and have set traps for me along my path. Selah
19Ps 140:6 O LORD, I say to you, "You are my God." Hear, O LORD, my cry for mercy.
19Ps 140:7 O Sovereign LORD, my strong deliverer, who shields my head in the day of battle--
19Ps 140:8 do not grant the wicked their desires, O LORD; do not let their plans succeed, or they will become proud. Selah
19Ps 140:9 Let the heads of those who surround me be covered with the trouble their lips have caused.
19Ps 140:10 Let burning coals fall upon them; may they be thrown into the fire, into miry pits, never to rise.
19Ps 140:11 Let slanderers not be established in the land; may disaster hunt down men of violence.
19Ps 140:12 I know that the LORD secures justice for the poor and upholds the cause of the needy.
19Ps 140:13 Surely the righteous will praise your name and the upright will live before you.
19Ps 141:1 A psalm of David. O LORD, I call to you; come quickly to me. Hear my voice when I call to you.
19Ps 141:2 May my prayer be set before you like incense; may the lifting up of my hands be like the evening sacrifice.
19Ps 141:3 Set a guard over my mouth, O LORD; keep watch over the door of my lips.
19Ps 141:4 Let not my heart be drawn to what is evil, to take part in wicked deeds with men who are evildoers; let me not eat of their delicacies.
19Ps 141:5 Let a righteous man strike me--it is a kindness; let him rebuke me--it is oil on my head. My head will not refuse it. Yet my prayer is ever against the deeds of evildoers;
19Ps 141:6 their rulers will be thrown down from the cliffs, and the wicked will learn that my words were well spoken.
19Ps 141:7 They will say,"As one plows and breaks up the earth, so our bones have been scattered at the mouth of the grave."
19Ps 141:8 But my eyes are fixed on you, O Sovereign LORD; in you I take refuge--do not give me over to death.
19Ps 141:9 Keep me from the snares they have laid for me, from the traps set by evildoers.
19Ps 141:10 Let the wicked fall into their own nets, while I pass by in safety.
19Ps 142:1 A maskil of David. When he was in the cave. A prayer. I cry aloud to the LORD; I lift up my voice to the LORD for mercy.
19Ps 142:2 I pour out my complaint before him; before him I tell my trouble.
19Ps 142:3 When my spirit grows faint within me, it is you who know my way. In the path where I walk men have hidden a snare for me.
19Ps 142:4 Look to my right and see; no one is concerned for me. I have no refuge; no one cares for my life.
19Ps 142:5 I cry to you, O LORD; I say, "You are my refuge, my portion in the land of the living."
19Ps 142:6 Listen to my cry, for I am in desperate need; rescue me from those who pursue me, for they are too strong for me.
19Ps 142:7 Set me free from my prison, that I may praise your name. Then the righteous will gather about me because of your goodness to me.
19Ps 143:1 A psalm of David. O LORD, hear my prayer, listen to my cry for mercy; in your faithfulness and righteousness come to my relief.
19Ps 143:2 Do not bring your servant into judgment, for no one living is righteous before you.
19Ps 143:3 The enemy pursues me, he crushes me to the ground; he makes me dwell in darkness like those long dead.
19Ps 143:4 So my spirit grows faint within me; my heart within me is dismayed.
19Ps 143:5 I remember the days of long ago; I meditate on all your works and consider what your hands have done.
19Ps 143:6 I spread out my hands to you; my soul thirsts for you like a parched land. Selah
19Ps 143:7 Answer me quickly, O LORD; my spirit fails. Do not hide your face from me or I will be like those who go down to the pit.
19Ps 143:8 Let the morning bring me word of your unfailing love, for I have put my trust in you. Show me the way I should go, for to you I lift up my soul.
19Ps 143:9 Rescue me from my enemies, O LORD, for I hide myself in you.
19Ps 143:10 Teach me to do your will, for you are my God; may your good Spirit lead me on level ground.
19Ps 143:11 For your name's sake, O LORD, preserve my life; in your righteousness, bring me out of trouble.
19Ps 143:12 In your unfailing love, silence my enemies; destroy all my foes, for I am your servant.
19Ps 144:1 Of David. Praise be to the LORD my Rock, who trains my hands for war, my fingers for battle.
19Ps 144:2 He is my loving God and my fortress, my stronghold and my deliverer, my shield, in whom I take refuge, who subdues peoples under me.
19Ps 144:3 O LORD, what is man that you care for him, the son of man that you think of him?
19Ps 144:4 Man is like a breath; his days are like a fleeting shadow.
19Ps 144:5 Part your heavens, O LORD, and come down; touch the mountains, so that they smoke.
19Ps 144:6 Send forth lightning and scatter the enemies; shoot your arrows and rout them.
19Ps 144:7 Reach down your hand from on high; deliver me and rescue me from the mighty waters, from the hands of foreigners
19Ps 144:8 whose mouths are full of lies, whose right hands are deceitful.
19Ps 144:9 I will sing a new song to you, O God; on the ten-stringed lyre I will make music to you,
19Ps 144:10 to the One who gives victory to kings, who delivers his servant David from the deadly sword.
19Ps 144:11 Deliver me and rescue me from the hands of foreigners whose mouths are full of lies, whose right hands are deceitful.
19Ps 144:12 Then our sons in their youth will be like well-nurtured plants, and our daughters will be like pillars carved to adorn a palace.
19Ps 144:13 Our barns will be filled with every kind of provision. Our sheep will increase by thousands, by tens of thousands in our fields;
19Ps 144:14 our oxen will draw heavy loads. There will be no breaching of walls, no going into captivity, no cry of distress in our streets.
19Ps 144:15 Blessed are the people of whom this is true; blessed are the people whose God is the LORD.
19Ps 145:1 A psalm of praise. Of David. I will exalt you, my God the King; I will praise your name for ever and ever.
19Ps 145:2 Every day I will praise you and extol your name for ever and ever.
19Ps 145:3 Great is the LORD and most worthy of praise; his greatness no one can fathom.
19Ps 145:4 One generation will commend your works to another; they will tell of your mighty acts.
19Ps 145:5 They will speak of the glorious splendor of your majesty, and I will meditate on your wonderful works.
19Ps 145:6 They will tell of the power of your awesome works, and I will proclaim your great deeds.
19Ps 145:7 They will celebrate your abundant goodness and joyfully sing of your righteousness.
19Ps 145:8 The LORD is gracious and compassionate, slow to anger and rich in love.
19Ps 145:9 The LORD is good to all; he has compassion on all he has made.
19Ps 145:10 All you have made will praise you, O LORD; your saints will extol you.
19Ps 145:11 They will tell of the glory of your kingdom and speak of your might,
19Ps 145:12 so that all men may know of your mighty acts and the glorious splendor of your kingdom.
19Ps 145:13 Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and your dominion endures through all generations. The LORD is faithful to all his promises and loving toward all he has made.
19Ps 145:14 The LORD upholds all those who fall and lifts up all who are bowed down.
19Ps 145:15 The eyes of all look to you, and you give them their food at the proper time.
19Ps 145:16 You open your hand and satisfy the desires of every living thing.
19Ps 145:17 The LORD is righteous in all his ways and loving toward all he has made.
19Ps 145:18 The LORD is near to all who call on him, to all who call on him in truth.
19Ps 145:19 He fulfills the desires of those who fear him; he hears their cry and saves them.
19Ps 145:20 The LORD watches over all who love him, but all the wicked he will destroy.
19Ps 145:21 My mouth will speak in praise of the LORD. Let every creature praise his holy name for ever and ever.
19Ps 146:1 Praise the LORD. Praise the LORD, O my soul.
19Ps 146:2 I will praise the LORD all my life; I will sing praise to my God as long as I live.
19Ps 146:3 Do not put your trust in princes, in mortal men, who cannot save.
19Ps 146:4 When their spirit departs, they return to the ground; on that very day their plans come to nothing.
19Ps 146:5 Blessed is he whose help is the God of Jacob, whose hope is in the LORD his God,
19Ps 146:6 the Maker of heaven and earth, the sea, and everything in them--the LORD, who remains faithful forever.
19Ps 146:7 He upholds the cause of the oppressed and gives food to the hungry. The LORD sets prisoners free,
19Ps 146:8 the LORD gives sight to the blind, the LORD lifts up those who are bowed down, the LORD loves the righteous.
19Ps 146:9 The LORD watches over the alien and sustains the fatherless and the widow, but he frustrates the ways of the wicked.
19Ps 146:10 The LORD reigns forever, your God, O Zion, for all generations. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 147:1 Praise the LORD. How good it is to sing praises to our God, how pleasant and fitting to praise him!
19Ps 147:2 The LORD builds up Jerusalem; he gathers the exiles of Israel.
19Ps 147:3 He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds.
19Ps 147:4 He determines the number of the stars and calls them each by name.
19Ps 147:5 Great is our Lord and mighty in power; his understanding has no limit.
19Ps 147:6 The LORD sustains the humble but casts the wicked to the ground.
19Ps 147:7 Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; make music to our God on the harp.
19Ps 147:8 He covers the sky with clouds; he supplies the earth with rain and makes grass grow on the hills.
19Ps 147:9 He provides food for the cattle and for the young ravens when they call.
19Ps 147:10 His pleasure is not in the strength of the horse, nor his delight in the legs of a man;
19Ps 147:11 the LORD delights in those who fear him, who put their hope in his unfailing love.
19Ps 147:12 Extol the LORD, O Jerusalem; praise your God, O Zion,
19Ps 147:13 for he strengthens the bars of your gates and blesses your people within you.
19Ps 147:14 He grants peace to your borders and satisfies you with the finest of wheat.
19Ps 147:15 He sends his command to the earth; his word runs swiftly.
19Ps 147:16 He spreads the snow like wool and scatters the frost like ashes.
19Ps 147:17 He hurls down his hail like pebbles. Who can withstand his icy blast?
19Ps 147:18 He sends his word and melts them; he stirs up his breezes, and the waters flow.
19Ps 147:19 He has revealed his word to Jacob, his laws and decrees to Israel.
19Ps 147:20 He has done this for no other nation; they do not know his laws. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 148:1 Praise the LORD. Praise the LORD from the heavens, praise him in the heights above.
19Ps 148:2 Praise him, all his angels, praise him, all his heavenly hosts.
19Ps 148:3 Praise him, sun and moon, praise him, all you shining stars.
19Ps 148:4 Praise him, you highest heavens and you waters above the skies.
19Ps 148:5 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for he commanded and they were created.
19Ps 148:6 He set them in place for ever and ever; he gave a decree that will never pass away.
19Ps 148:7 Praise the LORD from the earth, you great sea creatures and all ocean depths,
19Ps 148:8 lightning and hail, snow and clouds, stormy winds that do his bidding,
19Ps 148:9 you mountains and all hills, fruit trees and all cedars,
19Ps 148:10 wild animals and all cattle, small creatures and flying birds,
19Ps 148:11 kings of the earth and all nations, you princes and all rulers on earth,
19Ps 148:12 young men and maidens, old men and children.
19Ps 148:13 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for his name alone is exalted; his splendor is above the earth and the heavens.
19Ps 148:14 He has raised up for his people a horn, the praise of all his saints, of Israel, the people close to his heart. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 149:1 Praise the LORD. Sing to the LORD a new song, his praise in the assembly of the saints.
19Ps 149:2 Let Israel rejoice in their Maker; let the people of Zion be glad in their King.
19Ps 149:3 Let them praise his name with dancing and make music to him with tambourine and harp.
19Ps 149:4 For the LORD takes delight in his people; he crowns the humble with salvation.
19Ps 149:5 Let the saints rejoice in this honor and sing for joy on their beds.
19Ps 149:6 May the praise of God be in their mouths and a double-edged sword in their hands,
19Ps 149:7 to inflict vengeance on the nations and punishment on the peoples,
19Ps 149:8 to bind their kings with fetters, their nobles with shackles of iron,
19Ps 149:9 to carry out the sentence written against them. This is the glory of all his saints. Praise the LORD.
19Ps 150:1 Praise the LORD. Praise God in his sanctuary; praise him in his mighty heavens.
19Ps 150:2 Praise him for his acts of power; praise him for his surpassing greatness.
19Ps 150:3 Praise him with the sounding of the trumpet, praise him with the harp and lyre,
19Ps 150:4 praise him with tambourine and dancing, praise him with the strings and flute,
19Ps 150:5 praise him with the clash of cymbals, praise him with resounding cymbals.
19Ps 150:6 Let everything that has breath praise the LORD. Praise the LORD.
